var book = {
	"name": "Exodus",
	"numChapters": 40,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>Now these are the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1534A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1534A\"></sup>names of the sons of Israel who came to Egypt with Jacob; they came each one with his household:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Reuben, Simeon, Levi and Judah;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Issachar, Zebulun and Benjamin;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Dan and Naphtali, Gad and Asher.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>All the persons who came from the loins of Jacob were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1538B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1538B\"></sup>seventy in number, but Joseph was <i>already</i> in Egypt.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1539C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1539C\"></sup>Joseph died, and all his brothers and all that generation.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But the sons of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1540D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1540D\"></sup>were fruitful and increased greatly, and multiplied, and became exceedingly mighty, so that the land was filled with them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now a new <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1541E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1541E\"></sup>king arose over Egypt, who did not know Joseph.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1542F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1542F\"></sup>He said to his people, “Behold, the people of the sons of Israel are more and mightier than we.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Come, let us <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1543G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1543G\"></sup>deal wisely with them, or else they will multiply and in the event of war, they will also join themselves to those who hate us, and fight against us and depart from the land.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So they appointed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1544H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1544H\"></sup>taskmasters over them to afflict them with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1544I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1544I\"></sup>hard labor. And they built for Pharaoh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1544J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1544J\"></sup>storage cities, Pithom and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1544K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1544K\"></sup>Raamses.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But the more they afflicted them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1545L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1545L\"></sup>the more they multiplied and the more they spread out, so that they were in dread of the sons of Israel.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The Egyptians compelled the sons of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1546M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1546M\"></sup>to labor rigorously;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and they made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1547N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1547N\"></sup>their lives bitter with hard labor in mortar and bricks and at all <i>kinds</i> of labor in the field, all their labors which they rigorously imposed on them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the king of Egypt spoke to the Hebrew midwives, one of whom was named Shiphrah and the other was named Puah;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and he said, “When you are helping the Hebrew women to give birth and see <i>them</i> upon the birthstool, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1549O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1549O\"></sup>if it is a son, then you shall put him to death; but if it is a daughter, then she shall live.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But the midwives <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1550P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1550P\"></sup>feared God, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1550Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1550Q\"></sup>did not do as the king of Egypt had commanded them, but let the boys live.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So the king of Egypt called for the midwives and said to them, “Why have you done this thing, and let the boys live?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The midwives said to Pharaoh, “Because the Hebrew women are not as the Egyptian women; for they are vigorous and give birth before the midwife can get to them.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1553R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1553R\"></sup>God was good to the midwives, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1553S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1553S\"></sup>the people multiplied, and became very mighty.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Because the midwives <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1554T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1554T\"></sup>feared God, He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1554U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1554U\"></sup>established households for them.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Pharaoh commanded all his people, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1555V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1555V\"></sup>Every son who is born you are to cast into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1555W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1555W\"></sup>the Nile, and every daughter you are to keep alive.”"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>Now a man from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1556A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1556A\"></sup>the house of Levi went and married a daughter of Levi.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The woman conceived and bore a son; and when she saw that he was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1557B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1557B\"></sup>beautiful, she hid him for three months.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But when she could hide him no longer, she got him a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1558C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1558C\"></sup>wicker basket and covered it over with tar and pitch. Then she put the child into it and set <i>it</i> among the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1558D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1558D\"></sup>reeds by the bank of the Nile.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1559E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1559E\"></sup>His sister stood at a distance to find out what would happen to him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The daughter of Pharaoh came down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1560F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1560F\"></sup>to bathe at the Nile, with her maidens walking alongside the Nile; and she saw the basket among the reeds and sent her maid, and she brought it <i>to her</i>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When she opened <i>it</i>, she saw the child, and behold, <i>the</i> boy was crying. And she had pity on him and said, “This is one of the Hebrews’ children.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then his sister said to Pharaoh’s daughter, “Shall I go and call a nurse for you from the Hebrew women that she may nurse the child for you?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Pharaoh’s daughter said to her, “Go <i>ahead</i>.” So the girl went and called the child’s mother.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Pharaoh’s daughter said to her, “Take this child away and nurse him for me and I will give <i>you</i> your wages.” So the woman took the child and nursed him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The child grew, and she brought him to Pharaoh’s daughter and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1565G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1565G\"></sup>he became her son. And she named him Moses, and said, “Because I drew him out of the water.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now it came about in those days, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1566H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1566H\"></sup>when Moses had grown up, that he went out to his brethren and looked on their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1566I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1566I\"></sup>hard labors; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1566J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1566J\"></sup>he saw an Egyptian beating a Hebrew, one of his brethren.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So he looked this way and that, and when he saw there was no one <i>around</i>, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1567K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1567K\"></sup>struck down the Egyptian and hid him in the sand.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He went out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1568L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1568L\"></sup>the next day, and behold, two Hebrews were fighting with each other; and he said to the offender, “Why are you striking your companion?”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1569M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1569M\"></sup>Who made you a prince or a judge over us? Are you intending to kill me as you killed the Egyptian?” Then Moses was afraid and said, “Surely the matter has become known.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When Pharaoh heard of this matter, he tried to kill Moses. But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1570N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1570N\"></sup>Moses fled from the presence of Pharaoh and settled in the land of Midian, and he sat down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1570O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1570O\"></sup>by a well.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1571P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1571P\"></sup>the priest of Midian had seven daughters; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1571Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1571Q\"></sup>they came to draw water and filled the troughs to water their father’s flock.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then the shepherds came and drove them away, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1572R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1572R\"></sup>Moses stood up and helped them and watered their flock.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When they came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1573S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1573S\"></sup>Reuel their father, he said, “Why have you come <i>back</i> so soon today?”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So they said, “An Egyptian delivered us from the hand of the shepherds, and what is more, he even drew the water for us and watered the flock.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>He said to his daughters, “Where is he then? Why is it that you have left the man behind? Invite him to have something to eat.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1576T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1576T\"></sup>Moses was willing to dwell with the man, and he gave his daughter <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1576U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1576U\"></sup>Zipporah to Moses.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then she gave birth to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1577V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1577V\"></sup>a son, and he named him Gershom, for he said, “I have been <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1577W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1577W\"></sup>a sojourner in a foreign land.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now it came about in <i>the course of</i> those many days that the king of Egypt died. And the sons of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1578X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1578X\"></sup>sighed because of the bondage, and they cried out; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1578Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1578Y\"></sup>their cry for help because of <i>their</i> bondage rose up to God.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1579Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1579Z\"></sup>God heard their groaning; and God remembered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1579AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1579AA\"></sup>His covenant with Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1580AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1580AB\"></sup>God saw the sons of Israel, and God took notice <i>of them</i>."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Now Moses was pasturing the flock of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1581A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1581A\"></sup>Jethro his father-in-law, the priest of Midian; and he led the flock to the west side of the wilderness and came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1581B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1581B\"></sup>Horeb, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1581C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1581C\"></sup>mountain of God.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1582D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1582D\"></sup>The angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared to him in a blazing fire from the midst of a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1582E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1582E\"></sup>bush; and he looked, and behold, the bush was burning with fire, yet the bush was not consumed.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So Moses said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1583F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1583F\"></sup>I must turn aside now and see this marvelous sight, why the bush is not burned up.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saw that he turned aside to look, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1584G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1584G\"></sup>God called to him from the midst of the bush and said, “Moses, Moses!” And he said, “Here I am.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then He said, “Do not come near here; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1585H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1585H\"></sup>remove your sandals from your feet, for the place on which you are standing is holy ground.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He said also, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1586I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1586I\"></sup>I am the God of your father, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1586J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1586J\"></sup>Then Moses hid his face, for he was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1586K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1586K\"></sup>afraid to look at God.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “I have surely <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1587L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1587L\"></sup>seen the affliction of My people who are in Egypt, and have given heed to their cry because of their taskmasters, for I am aware of their sufferings.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So I have come down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1588M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1588M\"></sup>to deliver them from the power of the Egyptians, and to bring them up from that land to a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1588N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1588N\"></sup>good and spacious land, to a land flowing with milk and honey, to the place of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1588O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1588O\"></sup>the Canaanite and the Hittite and the Amorite and the Perizzite and the Hivite and the Jebusite.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1589P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1589P\"></sup>the cry of the sons of Israel has come to Me; furthermore, I have seen the oppression with which the Egyptians are oppressing them.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Therefore, come now, and I will send you to Pharaoh, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1590Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1590Q\"></sup>so that you may bring My people, the sons of Israel, out of Egypt.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But Moses said to God, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1591R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1591R\"></sup>Who am I, that I should go to Pharaoh, and that I should bring the sons of Israel out of Egypt?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And He said, “Certainly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1592S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1592S\"></sup>I will be with you, and this shall be the sign to you that it is I who have sent you: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1592T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1592T\"></sup>when you have brought the people out of Egypt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1592U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1592U\"></sup>you shall worship God at this mountain.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then Moses said to God, “Behold, I am going to the sons of Israel, and I will say to them, ‘The God of your fathers has sent me to you.’ Now they may say to me, ‘What is His name?’ What shall I say to them?”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>God said to Moses, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1594V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1594V\"></sup>I AM WHO I AM”; and He said, “Thus you shall say to the sons of Israel, ‘I AM has sent me to you.’”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>God, furthermore, said to Moses, “Thus you shall say to the sons of Israel, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1595W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1595W\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, has sent me to you.’ This is My name forever, and this is My <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1595X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1595X\"></sup>memorial-name to all generations.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Go and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1596Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1596Y\"></sup>gather the elders of Israel together and say to them, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1596Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1596Z\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your fathers, the God of Abraham, Isaac and Jacob, has appeared to me, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1596AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1596AA\"></sup>I am indeed concerned about you and what has been done to you in Egypt.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1597AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1597AB\"></sup>I said, I will bring you up out of the affliction of Egypt to the land of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1597AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1597AC\"></sup>the Canaanite and the Hittite and the Amorite and the Perizzite and the Hivite and the Jebusite, to a land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1597AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1597AD\"></sup>flowing with milk and honey.”’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1598AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1598AE\"></sup>They will pay heed to what you say; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1598AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1598AF\"></sup>you with the elders of Israel will come to the king of Egypt and you will say to him, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of the Hebrews, has met with us. So now, please, let us go a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1598AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1598AG\"></sup>three days’ journey into the wilderness, that we may sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God.’",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But I know that the king of Egypt <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1599AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1599AH\"></sup>will not permit you to go, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1599AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1599AI\"></sup>except under compulsion.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So I will stretch out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1600AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1600AJ\"></sup>My hand and strike Egypt with all My <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1600AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1600AK\"></sup>miracles which I shall do in the midst of it; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1600AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1600AL\"></sup>after that he will let you go.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>I will grant this people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1601AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1601AM\"></sup>favor in the sight of the Egyptians; and it shall be that when you go, you will not go empty-handed.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But every woman <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1602AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1602AN\"></sup>shall ask of her neighbor and the woman who lives in her house, articles of silver and articles of gold, and clothing; and you will put them on your sons and daughters. Thus you will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1602AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1602AO\"></sup>plunder the Egyptians.”"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Then Moses said, “What if they will not believe me or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1603A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1603A\"></sup>listen to what I say? For they may say, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1603B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1603B\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has not appeared to you.’”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “What is that in your hand?” And he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1604C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1604C\"></sup>A staff.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then He said, “Throw it on the ground.” So he threw it on the ground, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1605D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1605D\"></sup>it became a serpent; and Moses fled from it.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Stretch out your hand and grasp <i>it</i> by its tail”—so he stretched out his hand and caught it, and it became a staff in his hand—",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1607E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1607E\"></sup>they may believe that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1607F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1607F\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of their fathers, the God of Abraham, the God of Isaac, and the God of Jacob, has appeared to you.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> furthermore said to him, “Now put your hand into your bosom.” So he put his hand into his bosom, and when he took it out, behold, his hand was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1608G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1608G\"></sup>leprous like snow.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then He said, “Put your hand into your bosom again.” So he put his hand into his bosom again, and when he took it out of his bosom, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1609H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1609H\"></sup>it was restored like <i>the rest of</i> his flesh.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“If they will not believe you or heed the witness of the first sign, they may believe the witness of the last sign.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But if they will not believe even these two signs or heed what you say, then you shall take some water from the Nile and pour it on the dry ground; and the water which you take from the Nile <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1611I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1611I\"></sup>will become blood on the dry ground.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Moses said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Please, Lord, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1612J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1612J\"></sup>I have never been eloquent, neither recently nor in time past, nor since You have spoken to Your servant; for I am slow of speech and slow of tongue.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Who has made man’s mouth? Or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1613K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1613K\"></sup>who makes <i>him</i> mute or deaf, or seeing or blind? Is it not I, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now then go, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1614L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1614L\"></sup>I, even I, will be with your mouth, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1614M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1614M\"></sup>teach you what you are to say.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But he said, “Please, Lord, now send <i>the message</i> by whomever You will.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> burned against Moses, and He said, “Is there not your brother Aaron the Levite? I know that he speaks fluently. And moreover, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1616N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1616N\"></sup>he is coming out to meet you; when he sees you, he will be glad in his heart.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>You are to speak to him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1617O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1617O\"></sup>put the words in his mouth; and I, even I, will be with your mouth and his mouth, and I will teach you what you are to do.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1618P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1618P\"></sup>he shall speak for you to the people; and he will be as a mouth for you and you will be as God to him.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>You shall take in your hand <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1619Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1619Q\"></sup>this staff, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1619R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1619R\"></sup>with which you shall perform the signs.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Moses departed and returned to Jethro <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1620S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1620S\"></sup>his father-in-law and said to him, “Please, let me go, that I may return to my brethren who are in Egypt, and see if they are still alive.” And Jethro said to Moses, “Go in peace.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses in Midian, “Go back to Egypt, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1621T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1621T\"></sup>all the men who were seeking your life are dead.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Moses took his wife and his <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1622U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1622U\"></sup>sons and mounted them on a donkey, and returned to the land of Egypt. Moses also took the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1622V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1622V\"></sup>staff of God in his hand.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “When you go back to Egypt see that you perform before Pharaoh all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1623W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1623W\"></sup>the wonders which I have put in your power; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1623X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1623X\"></sup>I will harden his heart so that he will not let the people go.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then you shall say to Pharaoh, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1624Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1624Y\"></sup>Israel is My son, My firstborn.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So I said to you, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1625Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1625Z\"></sup>Let My son go that he may serve Me’; but you have refused to let him go. Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1625AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1625AA\"></sup>I will kill your son, your firstborn.”’”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Now it came about at the lodging place on the way that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> met him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1626AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1626AB\"></sup>sought to put him to death.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then Zipporah took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1627AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1627AC\"></sup>a flint and cut off her son’s foreskin and threw it at Moses’ feet, and she said, “You are indeed a bridegroom of blood to me.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So He let him alone. At that time she said, “<i>You are</i> a bridegroom of blood”—because of the circumcision.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1629AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1629AD\"></sup>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Aaron, “Go to meet Moses in the wilderness.” So he went and met him at the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1629AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1629AE\"></sup>mountain of God and kissed him.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1630AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1630AF\"></sup>Moses told Aaron all the words of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with which He had sent him, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1630AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1630AG\"></sup>all the signs that He had commanded him <i>to do</i>.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Moses and Aaron went and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1631AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1631AH\"></sup>assembled all the elders of the sons of Israel;",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1632AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1632AI\"></sup>Aaron spoke all the words which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had spoken to Moses. He then performed the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1632AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1632AJ\"></sup>signs in the sight of the people.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1633AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1633AK\"></sup>the people believed; and when they heard that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1633AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1633AL\"></sup>was concerned about the sons of Israel and that He had seen their affliction, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1633AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1633AM\"></sup>they bowed low and worshiped."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>And afterward Moses and Aaron came and said to Pharaoh, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1634A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1634A\"></sup>Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1634B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1634B\"></sup>Let My people go that they may celebrate a feast to Me in the wilderness.’”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But Pharaoh said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1635C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1635C\"></sup>Who is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that I should obey His voice to let Israel go? I do not know the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and besides, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1635D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1635D\"></sup>I will not let Israel go.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then they said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1636E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1636E\"></sup>The God of the Hebrews has met with us. Please, let us go a three days’ journey into the wilderness that we may sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, otherwise He will fall upon us with pestilence or with the sword.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But the king of Egypt said to them, “Moses and Aaron, why do you draw the people away from their work? Get <i>back</i> to your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1637F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1637F\"></sup>labors!”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Again Pharaoh said, “Look, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1638G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1638G\"></sup>the people of the land are now many, and you would have them cease from their labors!”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So the same day Pharaoh commanded <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1639H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1639H\"></sup>the taskmasters over the people and their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1639I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1639I\"></sup>foremen, saying,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“You are no longer to give the people straw to make brick as previously; let them go and gather straw for themselves.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But the quota of bricks which they were making previously, you shall impose on them; you are not to reduce any of it. Because they are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1641J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1641J\"></sup>lazy, therefore they cry out, ‘Let us go and sacrifice to our God.’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Let the labor be heavier on the men, and let them work at it so that they will pay no attention to false words.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1643K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1643K\"></sup>the taskmasters of the people and their foremen went out and spoke to the people, saying, “Thus says Pharaoh, ‘I am not going to give you <i>any</i> straw.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You go <i>and</i> get straw for yourselves wherever you can find <i>it</i>, but none of your labor will be reduced.’”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So the people scattered through all the land of Egypt to gather stubble for straw.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The taskmasters pressed them, saying, “Complete your work quota, <i>your</i> daily amount, just as when you had straw.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1647L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1647L\"></sup>the foremen of the sons of Israel, whom Pharaoh’s taskmasters had set over them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1647M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1647M\"></sup>were beaten and were asked, “Why have you not completed your required amount either yesterday or today in making brick as previously?”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the foremen of the sons of Israel came and cried out to Pharaoh, saying, “Why do you deal this way with your servants?",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>There is no straw given to your servants, yet they keep saying to us, ‘Make bricks!’ And behold, your servants are being beaten; but it is the fault of your <i>own</i> people.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But he said, “You are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1650N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1650N\"></sup>lazy, <i>very</i> lazy; therefore you say, ‘Let us go <i>and</i> sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So go now <i>and</i> work; for you will be given no straw, yet you must deliver the quota of bricks.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The foremen of the sons of Israel saw that they were in trouble because they were told, “You must not reduce <i>your</i> daily amount of bricks.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>When they left Pharaoh’s presence, they met Moses and Aaron as they were waiting for them.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1654O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1654O\"></sup>They said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1654P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1654P\"></sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> look upon you and judge <i>you</i>, for you have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1654Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1654Q\"></sup>made us odious in Pharaoh’s sight and in the sight of his servants, to put a sword in their hand to kill us.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then Moses returned to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1655R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1655R\"></sup>O Lord, why have You brought harm to this people? Why did You ever send me?",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Ever since I came to Pharaoh to speak in Your name, he has done harm to this people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1656S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1656S\"></sup>and You have not delivered Your people at all.”"
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Now you shall see what I will do to Pharaoh; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1657A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1657A\"></sup>under compulsion he will let them go, and under compulsion he will drive them out of his land.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>God spoke further to Moses and said to him, “I am <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1658B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1658B\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and I appeared to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1659C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1659C\"></sup>God Almighty, but <i>by</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1659D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1659D\"></sup>My name, <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I did not make Myself known to them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>I also established <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1660E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1660E\"></sup>My covenant with them, to give them the land of Canaan, the land in which they sojourned.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Furthermore I have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1661F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1661F\"></sup>heard the groaning of the sons of Israel, because the Egyptians are holding them in bondage, and I have remembered My covenant.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Say, therefore, to the sons of Israel, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1662G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1662G\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1662H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1662H\"></sup>I will bring you out from under the burdens of the Egyptians, and I will deliver you from their bondage. I will also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1662I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1662I\"></sup>redeem you with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1662J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1662J\"></sup>an outstretched arm and with great judgments.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then I will take you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1663K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1663K\"></sup>for My people, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1663L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1663L\"></sup>I will be your God; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1663M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1663M\"></sup>you shall know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who brought you out from under the burdens of the Egyptians.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I will bring you to the land which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1664N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1664N\"></sup>I swore to give to Abraham, Isaac, and Jacob, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1664O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1664O\"></sup>I will give it to you <i>for</i> a possession; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1664P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1664P\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So Moses spoke thus to the sons of Israel, but they did not listen to Moses on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1665Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1665Q\"></sup>account of <i>their</i> despondency and cruel bondage.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1667R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1667R\"></sup>Go, tell Pharaoh king of Egypt to let the sons of Israel go out of his land.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But Moses spoke before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, “Behold, the sons of Israel have not listened to me; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1668S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1668S\"></sup>how then will Pharaoh listen to me, for I am <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1668T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1668T\"></sup>unskilled in speech?”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses and to Aaron, and gave them a charge to the sons of Israel and to Pharaoh king of Egypt, to bring the sons of Israel out of the land of Egypt.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>These are the heads of their fathers’ households. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1670U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1670U\"></sup>The sons of Reuben, Israel’s firstborn: Hanoch and Pallu, Hezron and Carmi; these are the families of Reuben.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1671V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1671V\"></sup>sons of Simeon: Jemuel and Jamin and Ohad and Jachin and Zohar and Shaul the son of a Canaanite woman; these are the families of Simeon.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>These are the names of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1672W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1672W\"></sup>the sons of Levi according to their generations: Gershon and Kohath and Merari; and the length of Levi’s life was one hundred and thirty-seven years.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1673X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1673X\"></sup>The sons of Gershon: Libni and Shimei, according to their families.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1674Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1674Y\"></sup>The sons of Kohath: Amram and Izhar and Hebron and Uzziel; and the length of Kohath’s life was one hundred and thirty-three years.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1675Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1675Z\"></sup>The sons of Merari: Mahli and Mushi. These are the families of the Levites according to their generations.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1676AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1676AA\"></sup>Amram married his father’s sister Jochebed, and she bore him Aaron and Moses; and the length of Amram’s life was one hundred and thirty-seven years.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1677AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1677AB\"></sup>The sons of Izhar: Korah and Nepheg and Zichri.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1678AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1678AC\"></sup>The sons of Uzziel: Mishael and Elzaphan and Sithri.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Aaron married Elisheba, the daughter of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1679AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1679AD\"></sup>Amminadab, the sister of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1679AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1679AE\"></sup>Nahshon, and she bore him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1679AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1679AF\"></sup>Nadab and Abihu, Eleazar and Ithamar.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1680AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1680AG\"></sup>sons of Korah: Assir and Elkanah and Abiasaph; these are the families of the Korahites.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Aaron’s son <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1681AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1681AH\"></sup>Eleazar married one of the daughters of Putiel, and she bore him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1681AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1681AI\"></sup>Phinehas. These are the heads of the fathers’ <i>households</i> of the Levites according to their families.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>It was <i>the same</i> Aaron and Moses to whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1682AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1682AJ\"></sup>Bring out the sons of Israel from the land of Egypt according to their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1682AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1682AK\"></sup>hosts.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>They were the ones <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1683AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1683AL\"></sup>who spoke to Pharaoh king of Egypt about bringing out the sons of Israel from Egypt; it was <i>the same</i> Moses and Aaron.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now it came about on the day when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses in the land of Egypt,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1685AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1685AM\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1685AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1685AN\"></sup>speak to Pharaoh king of Egypt all that I speak to you.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>But Moses said before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “Behold, I am <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1686AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1686AO\"></sup>unskilled in speech; how then will Pharaoh listen to me?”"
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1687A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1687A\"></sup>See, I make you <i>as</i> God to Pharaoh, and your brother Aaron shall be your prophet.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>You shall speak all that I command you, and your brother <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1688B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1688B\"></sup>Aaron shall speak to Pharaoh that he let the sons of Israel go out of his land.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1689C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1689C\"></sup>I will harden Pharaoh’s heart that I may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1689D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1689D\"></sup>multiply My signs and My wonders in the land of Egypt.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1690E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1690E\"></sup>Pharaoh does not listen to you, then I will lay My hand on Egypt and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1690F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1690F\"></sup>bring out My hosts, My people the sons of Israel, from the land of Egypt by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1690G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1690G\"></sup>great judgments.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1691H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1691H\"></sup>The Egyptians shall know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, when I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1691I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1691I\"></sup>stretch out My hand on Egypt and bring out the sons of Israel from their midst.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Moses and Aaron did <i>it</i>; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1692J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1692J\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded them, thus they did.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Moses was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1693K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1693K\"></sup>eighty years old and Aaron eighty-three, when they spoke to Pharaoh.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses and Aaron, saying,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“When Pharaoh speaks to you, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1695L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1695L\"></sup>Work a miracle,’ then you shall say to Aaron, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1695M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1695M\"></sup>Take your staff and throw <i>it</i> down before Pharaoh, <i>that</i> it may become a serpent.’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So Moses and Aaron came to Pharaoh, and thus they did just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded; and Aaron threw his staff down before Pharaoh and his servants, and it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1696N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1696N\"></sup>became a serpent.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Pharaoh also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1697O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1697O\"></sup>called for <i>the</i> wise men and <i>the</i> sorcerers, and they also, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1697P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1697P\"></sup>magicians of Egypt, did the same with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1697Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1697Q\"></sup>their secret arts.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For each one threw down his staff and they turned into serpents. But Aaron’s staff swallowed up their staffs.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1699R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1699R\"></sup>Pharaoh’s heart was hardened, and he did not listen to them, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Pharaoh’s heart is stubborn; he refuses to let the people go.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Go to Pharaoh in the morning as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1701S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1701S\"></sup>he is going out to the water, and station yourself to meet him on the bank of the Nile; and you shall take in your hand <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1701T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1701T\"></sup>the staff that was turned into a serpent.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1702U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1702U\"></sup>You shall say to him, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of the Hebrews, sent me to you, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1702V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1702V\"></sup>Let My people go, that they may serve Me in the wilderness. But behold, you have not listened until now.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1703W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1703W\"></sup>By this you shall know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: behold, I will strike the water that is in the Nile with the staff that is in my hand, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1703X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1703X\"></sup>it will be turned to blood.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1704Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1704Y\"></sup>The fish that are in the Nile will die, and the Nile will become foul, and the Egyptians will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1704Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1704Z\"></sup>find difficulty in drinking water from the Nile.”’”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Say to Aaron, ‘Take your staff and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1705AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1705AA\"></sup>stretch out your hand over the waters of Egypt, over their rivers, over their streams, and over their pools, and over all their reservoirs of water, that they may become blood; and there will be blood throughout all the land of Egypt, both in <i>vessels of</i> wood and in <i>vessels of</i> stone.’”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So Moses and Aaron did even as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded. And he lifted up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1706AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1706AB\"></sup>the staff and struck the water that <i>was</i> in the Nile, in the sight of Pharaoh and in the sight of his servants, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1706AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1706AC\"></sup>all the water that <i>was</i> in the Nile was turned to blood.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The fish that <i>were</i> in the Nile died, and the Nile became foul, so that the Egyptians could not drink water from the Nile. And the blood was through all the land of Egypt.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1708AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1708AD\"></sup>But the magicians of Egypt did the same with their secret arts; and Pharaoh’s heart was hardened, and he did not listen to them, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then Pharaoh turned and went into his house with no concern even for this.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So all the Egyptians dug around the Nile for water to drink, for they could not drink of the water of the Nile.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Seven days passed after the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had struck the Nile."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Go to Pharaoh and say to him, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1712A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1712A\"></sup>Let My people go, that they may serve Me.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>But if you refuse to let <i>them</i> go, behold, I will smite your whole territory with frogs.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The Nile will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1714B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1714B\"></sup>swarm with frogs, which will come up and go into your house and into your bedroom and on your bed, and into the houses of your servants and on your people, and into your ovens and into your kneading bowls.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So the frogs will come up on you and your people and all your servants.”’”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Say to Aaron, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1716C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1716C\"></sup>Stretch out your hand with your staff over the rivers, over the streams and over the pools, and make frogs come up on the land of Egypt.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Aaron stretched out his hand over the waters of Egypt, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1717D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1717D\"></sup>frogs came up and covered the land of Egypt.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1718E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1718E\"></sup>The magicians did the same with their secret arts, making frogs come up on the land of Egypt.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Pharaoh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1719F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1719F\"></sup>called for Moses and Aaron and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1719G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1719G\"></sup>Entreat the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that He remove the frogs from me and from my people; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1719H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1719H\"></sup>I will let the people go, that they may sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Moses said to Pharaoh, “The honor is yours to tell me: when shall I entreat for you and your servants and your people, that the frogs be destroyed from you and your houses, <i>that</i> they may be left only in the Nile?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then he said, “Tomorrow.” So he said, “<i>May it be</i> according to your word, that you may know that there is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1721I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1721I\"></sup>no one like the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1722J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1722J\"></sup>frogs will depart from you and your houses and your servants and your people; they will be left only in the Nile.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Moses and Aaron went out from Pharaoh, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1723K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1723K\"></sup>Moses cried to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> concerning the frogs which He had inflicted upon Pharaoh.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did according to the word of Moses, and the frogs died out of the houses, the courts, and the fields.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So they piled them in heaps, and the land became foul.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>But when Pharaoh saw that there was relief, he hardened his heart and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1726L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1726L\"></sup>did not listen to them, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Say to Aaron, ‘Stretch out your staff and strike the dust of the earth, that it may become gnats through all the land of Egypt.’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They did so; and Aaron stretched out his hand with his staff, and struck the dust of the earth, and there were gnats on man and beast. All the dust of the earth became <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1728M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1728M\"></sup>gnats through all the land of Egypt.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The magicians tried with their secret arts to bring forth gnats, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1729N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1729N\"></sup>they could not; so there were gnats on man and beast.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then the magicians said to Pharaoh, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1730O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1730O\"></sup>This is the finger of God.” But Pharaoh’s heart was hardened, and he did not listen to them, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1731P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1731P\"></sup>Rise early in the morning and present yourself before Pharaoh, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1731Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1731Q\"></sup>he comes out to the water, and say to him, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1731R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1731R\"></sup>Let My people go, that they may serve Me.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>For if you do not let My people go, behold, I will send swarms of flies on you and on your servants and on your people and into your houses; and the houses of the Egyptians will be full of swarms of flies, and also the ground on which they <i>dwell</i>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1733S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1733S\"></sup>But on that day I will set apart the land of Goshen, where My people are living, so that no swarms of flies will be there, in order that you may know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1733T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1733T\"></sup>I, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, am in the midst of the land.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>I will put a division between My people and your people. Tomorrow this sign will occur.”’”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did so. And there came great swarms of flies into the house of Pharaoh and the houses of his servants and the land was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1735U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1735U\"></sup>laid waste because of the swarms of flies in all the land of Egypt.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Pharaoh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1736V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1736V\"></sup>called for Moses and Aaron and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1736W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1736W\"></sup>Go, sacrifice to your God within the land.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But Moses said, “It is not right to do so, for we will sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God what is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1737X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1737X\"></sup>an abomination to the Egyptians. If we sacrifice what is an abomination to the Egyptians before their eyes, will they not then stone us?",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>We must go a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1738Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1738Y\"></sup>three days’ journey into the wilderness and sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God as He commands us.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Pharaoh said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1739Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1739Z\"></sup>I will let you go, that you may sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in the wilderness; only you shall not go very far away. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1739AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1739AA\"></sup>Make supplication for me.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Moses said, “Behold, I am going out from you, and I shall make supplication to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that the swarms of flies may depart from Pharaoh, from his servants, and from his people tomorrow; only do not let Pharaoh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1740AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1740AB\"></sup>deal deceitfully again in not letting the people go to sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1741AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1741AC\"></sup>Moses went out from Pharaoh and made supplication to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did as Moses asked, and removed the swarms of flies from Pharaoh, from his servants and from his people; not one remained.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But Pharaoh hardened his heart this time also, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1743AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1743AD\"></sup>he did not let the people go."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Go to Pharaoh and speak to him, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of the Hebrews, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1744A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1744A\"></sup>Let My people go, that they may serve Me.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1745B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1745B\"></sup>if you refuse to let <i>them</i> go and continue to hold them,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1746C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1746C\"></sup>the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will come <i>with</i> a very severe pestilence on your livestock which are in the field, on the horses, on the donkeys, on the camels, on the herds, and on the flocks.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1747D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1747D\"></sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will make a distinction between the livestock of Israel and the livestock of Egypt, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1747E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1747E\"></sup>nothing will die of all that belongs to the sons of Israel.”’”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> set a definite time, saying, “Tomorrow the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will do this thing in the land.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did this thing on the next day, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1749F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1749F\"></sup>all the livestock of Egypt died; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1749G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1749G\"></sup>but of the livestock of the sons of Israel, not one died.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Pharaoh sent, and behold, there was not even one of the livestock of Israel dead. But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1750H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1750H\"></sup>the heart of Pharaoh was hardened, and he did not let the people go.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses and Aaron, “Take for yourselves handfuls of soot from a kiln, and let Moses throw it toward the sky in the sight of Pharaoh.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>It will become fine dust over all the land of Egypt, and will become <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1752I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1752I\"></sup>boils breaking out with sores on man and beast through all the land of Egypt.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So they took soot from a kiln, and stood before Pharaoh; and Moses threw it toward the sky, and it became boils breaking out with sores on man and beast.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1754J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1754J\"></sup>The magicians could not stand before Moses because of the boils, for the boils were on the magicians as well as on all the Egyptians.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1755K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1755K\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> hardened Pharaoh’s heart, and he did not listen to them, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had spoken to Moses.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1756L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1756L\"></sup>Rise up early in the morning and stand before Pharaoh and say to him, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of the Hebrews, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1756M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1756M\"></sup>Let My people go, that they may serve Me.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For this time I will send all My plagues on you and your servants and your people, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1757N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1757N\"></sup>you may know that there is no one like Me in all the earth.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For <i>if by</i> now I had put forth My hand and struck you and your people with pestilence, you would then have been cut off from the earth.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But, indeed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1759O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1759O\"></sup>for this reason I have allowed you to remain, in order to show you My power and in order to proclaim My name through all the earth.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Still you exalt yourself against My people by not letting them go.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Behold, about this time tomorrow, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1761P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1761P\"></sup>I will send a very heavy hail, such as has not been <i>seen</i> in Egypt from the day it was founded until now.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now therefore send, bring <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1762Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1762Q\"></sup>your livestock and whatever you have in the field to safety. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1762R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1762R\"></sup>Every man and beast that is found in the field and is not brought home, when the hail comes down on them, will die.”’”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1763S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1763S\"></sup>The one among the servants of Pharaoh who feared the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made his servants and his livestock flee into the houses;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>but he who paid no regard to the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> left his servants and his livestock in the field.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Stretch out your hand toward the sky, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1765T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1765T\"></sup>hail may fall on all the land of Egypt, on man and on beast and on every plant of the field, throughout the land of Egypt.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Moses stretched out his staff toward the sky, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent thunder and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1766U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1766U\"></sup>hail, and fire ran down to the earth. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rained hail on the land of Egypt.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So there was hail, and fire flashing continually in the midst of the hail, very severe, such as had not been in all the land of Egypt since it became a nation.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1768V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1768V\"></sup>The hail struck all that was in the field through all the land of Egypt, both man and beast; the hail also struck every plant of the field and shattered every tree of the field.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1769W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1769W\"></sup>Only in the land of Goshen, where the sons of Israel <i>were</i>, there was no hail.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then Pharaoh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1770X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1770X\"></sup>sent for Moses and Aaron, and said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1770Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1770Y\"></sup>I have sinned this time; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is the righteous one, and I and my people are the wicked ones.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1771Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1771Z\"></sup>Make supplication to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for there has been enough of God’s thunder and hail; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1771AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1771AA\"></sup>I will let you go, and you shall stay no longer.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Moses said to him, “As soon as I go out of the city, I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1772AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1772AB\"></sup>spread out my hands to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; the thunder will cease and there will be hail no longer, that you may know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1772AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1772AC\"></sup>the earth is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span>.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1773AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1773AD\"></sup>But as for you and your servants, I know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1773AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1773AE\"></sup>you do not yet fear the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>(Now the flax and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1774AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1774AF\"></sup>barley were ruined, for the barley was in the ear and the flax was in bud.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But the wheat and the spelt were not ruined, for they <i>ripen</i> late.)",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1776AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1776AG\"></sup>So Moses went out of the city from Pharaoh, and spread out his hands to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and the thunder and the hail ceased, and rain no longer poured on the earth.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But when Pharaoh saw that the rain and the hail and the thunder had ceased, he sinned again and hardened his heart, he and his servants.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Pharaoh’s heart was hardened, and he did not let the sons of Israel go, just as the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1778AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1778AH\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had spoken through Moses."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Go to Pharaoh, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1779A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1779A\"></sup>I have hardened his heart and the heart of his servants, that I may perform these signs of Mine among them,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1780B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1780B\"></sup>that you may tell in the hearing of your son, and of your grandson, how I made a mockery of the Egyptians and how I performed My signs among them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1780C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1780C\"></sup>that you may know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Moses and Aaron went to Pharaoh and said to him, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of the Hebrews, ‘How long will you refuse to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1781D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1781D\"></sup>humble yourself before Me? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1781E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1781E\"></sup>Let My people go, that they may serve Me.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>For if you refuse to let My people go, behold, tomorrow I will bring locusts into your territory.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They shall cover the surface of the land, so that no one will be able to see the land. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1783F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1783F\"></sup>They will also eat the rest of what has escaped—what is left to you from the hail—and they will eat every tree which sprouts for you out of the field.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1784G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1784G\"></sup>your houses shall be filled and the houses of all your servants and the houses of all the Egyptians, <i>something</i> which neither your fathers nor your grandfathers have seen, from the day that they came upon the earth until this day.’” And he turned and went out from Pharaoh.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1785H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1785H\"></sup>Pharaoh’s servants said to him, “How long will this man be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1785I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1785I\"></sup>a snare to us? Let the men go, that they may serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God. Do you not realize that Egypt is destroyed?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Moses and Aaron <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1786J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1786J\"></sup>were brought back to Pharaoh, and he said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1786K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1786K\"></sup>Go, serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God! Who are the ones that are going?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Moses said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1787L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1787L\"></sup>We shall go with our young and our old; with our sons and our daughters, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1787M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1787M\"></sup>with our flocks and our herds we shall go, for we must hold a feast to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then he said to them, “Thus may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> be with you, if ever I let you and your little ones go! Take heed, for evil is in your mind.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Not so! Go now, the men <i>among you</i>, and serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for that is what you desire.” So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1789N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1789N\"></sup>they were driven out from Pharaoh’s presence.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1790O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1790O\"></sup>Stretch out your hand over the land of Egypt for the locusts, that they may come up on the land of Egypt and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1790P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1790P\"></sup>eat every plant of the land, <i>even</i> all that the hail has left.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Moses stretched out his staff over the land of Egypt, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> directed an east wind on the land all that day and all that night; and when it was morning, the east wind brought the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1791Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1791Q\"></sup>locusts.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1792R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1792R\"></sup>The locusts came up over all the land of Egypt and settled in all the territory of Egypt; <i>they were</i> very numerous. There had never been so <i>many</i> locusts, nor would there be so <i>many</i> again.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>For they covered the surface of the whole land, so that the land was darkened; and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1793S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1793S\"></sup>ate every plant of the land and all the fruit of the trees that the hail had left. Thus nothing green was left on tree or plant of the field through all the land of Egypt.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Pharaoh hurriedly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1794T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1794T\"></sup>called for Moses and Aaron, and he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1794U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1794U\"></sup>I have sinned against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God and against you.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now therefore, please forgive my sin only this once, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1795V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1795V\"></sup>make supplication to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, that He would only remove this death from me.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1796W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1796W\"></sup>He went out from Pharaoh and made supplication to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shifted <i>the wind</i> to a very strong west wind which took up the locusts and drove them into the Red Sea; not one locust was left in all the territory of Egypt.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1798X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1798X\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> hardened Pharaoh’s heart, and he did not let the sons of Israel go.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1799Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1799Y\"></sup>Stretch out your hand toward the sky, that there may be darkness over the land of Egypt, even a darkness <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1799Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1799Z\"></sup>which may be felt.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So Moses stretched out his hand toward the sky, and there was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1800AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1800AA\"></sup>thick darkness in all the land of Egypt for three days.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>They did not see one another, nor did anyone rise from his place for three days, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1801AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1801AB\"></sup>but all the sons of Israel had light in their dwellings.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Pharaoh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1802AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1802AC\"></sup>called to Moses, and said, “Go, serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; only let your flocks and your herds be detained. Even <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1802AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1802AD\"></sup>your little ones may go with you.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But Moses said, “You must also let us have sacrifices and burnt offerings, that we may sacrifice <i>them</i> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1804AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1804AE\"></sup>Therefore, our livestock too shall go with us; not a hoof shall be left behind, for we shall take some of them to serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God. And until we arrive there, we ourselves do not know with what we shall serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1805AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1805AF\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> hardened Pharaoh’s heart, and he was not willing to let them go.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then Pharaoh said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1806AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1806AG\"></sup>Get away from me! Beware, do not see my face again, for in the day you see my face you shall die!”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Moses said, “You are right; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1807AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1807AH\"></sup>I shall never see your face again!”"
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “One more plague I will bring on Pharaoh and on Egypt; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1808A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1808A\"></sup>after that he will let you go from here. When he lets you go, he will surely drive you out from here completely.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Speak now in the hearing of the people that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1809B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1809B\"></sup>each man ask from his neighbor and each woman from her neighbor for articles of silver and articles of gold.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1810C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1810C\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gave the people favor in the sight of the Egyptians. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1810D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1810D\"></sup>Furthermore, the man Moses <i>himself</i> was greatly esteemed in the land of Egypt, <i>both</i> in the sight of Pharaoh’s servants and in the sight of the people.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Moses said, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘About <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1811E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1811E\"></sup>midnight I am going out into the midst of Egypt,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1812F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1812F\"></sup>all the firstborn in the land of Egypt shall die, from the firstborn of the Pharaoh who sits on his throne, even to the firstborn of the slave girl who is behind the millstones; all the firstborn of the cattle as well.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Moreover, there shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1813G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1813G\"></sup>a great cry in all the land of Egypt, such as there has not been <i>before</i> and such as shall never be again.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1814H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1814H\"></sup>But against any of the sons of Israel a dog will not <i>even</i> bark, whether against man or beast, that you may understand how the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> makes a distinction between Egypt and Israel.’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1815I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1815I\"></sup>All these your servants will come down to me and bow themselves before me, saying, ‘Go out, you and all the people who follow you,’ and after that I will go out.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1815J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1815J\"></sup>And he went out from Pharaoh in hot anger.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1816K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1816K\"></sup>Pharaoh will not listen to you, so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1816L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1816L\"></sup>that My wonders will be multiplied in the land of Egypt.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1817M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1817M\"></sup>Moses and Aaron performed all these wonders before Pharaoh; yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1817N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1817N\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> hardened Pharaoh’s heart, and he did not let the sons of Israel go out of his land."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses and Aaron in the land of Egypt,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1819A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1819A\"></sup>This month shall be the beginning of months for you; it is to be the first month of the year to you.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Speak to all the congregation of Israel, saying, ‘On the tenth of this month they are each one to take a lamb for themselves, according to their fathers’ households, a lamb for each household.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now if the household is too small for a lamb, then he and his neighbor nearest to his house are to take one according to the number of persons <i>in them</i>; according to what each man should eat, you are to divide the lamb.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Your lamb shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1822B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1822B\"></sup>an unblemished male a year old; you may take it from the sheep or from the goats.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You shall keep it until the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1823C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1823C\"></sup>fourteenth day of the same month, then the whole assembly of the congregation of Israel is to kill it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1823D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1823D\"></sup>at twilight.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1824E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1824E\"></sup>Moreover, they shall take some of the blood and put it on the two doorposts and on the lintel of the houses in which they eat it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They shall eat the flesh <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1825F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1825F\"></sup>that <i>same</i> night, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1825G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1825G\"></sup>roasted with fire, and they shall eat it with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1825H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1825H\"></sup>unleavened bread <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1825I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1825I\"></sup>and bitter herbs.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Do not eat any of it raw or boiled at all with water, but rather <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1826J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1826J\"></sup>roasted with fire, <i>both</i> its head and its legs along with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1826K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1826K\"></sup>its entrails.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1827L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1827L\"></sup>And you shall not leave any of it over until morning, but whatever is left of it until morning, you shall burn with fire.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now you shall eat it in this manner: <i>with</i> your loins girded, your sandals on your feet, and your staff in your hand; and you shall eat it in haste—it is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1828M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1828M\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> Passover.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1829N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1829N\"></sup>I will go through the land of Egypt on that night, and will strike down all the firstborn in the land of Egypt, both man and beast; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1829O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1829O\"></sup>against all the gods of Egypt I will execute judgments—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1829P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1829P\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1830Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1830Q\"></sup>The blood shall be a sign for you on the houses where you live; and when I see the blood I will pass over you, and no plague will befall you to destroy <i>you</i> when I strike the land of Egypt.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>‘Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1831R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1831R\"></sup>this day will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1831S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1831S\"></sup>a memorial to you, and you shall celebrate it <i>as</i> a feast to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; throughout your generations you are to celebrate it <i>as</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1831T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1831T\"></sup>a permanent ordinance.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1832U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1832U\"></sup>Seven days you shall eat unleavened bread, but on the first day you shall remove leaven from your houses; for whoever eats anything leavened from the first day until the seventh day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1832V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1832V\"></sup>that person shall be cut off from Israel.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1833W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1833W\"></sup>On the first day you shall have a holy assembly, and <i>another</i> holy assembly on the seventh day; no work at all shall be done on them, except what must be eaten by every person, that alone may be prepared by you.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>You shall also observe <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1834X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1834X\"></sup>the <i>Feast of</i> Unleavened Bread, for on this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1834Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1834Y\"></sup>very day I brought your hosts out of the land of Egypt; therefore you shall observe this day throughout your generations as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1834Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1834Z\"></sup>a permanent ordinance.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1835AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1835AA\"></sup>In the first <i>month</i>, on the fourteenth day of the month at evening, you shall eat unleavened bread, until the twenty-first day of the month at evening.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1836AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1836AB\"></sup>Seven days there shall be no leaven found in your houses; for whoever eats what is leavened, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1836AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1836AC\"></sup>person shall be cut off from the congregation of Israel, whether <i>he is</i> an alien or a native of the land.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You shall not eat anything leavened; in all your dwellings you shall eat unleavened bread.’”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1838AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1838AD\"></sup>Moses called for all the elders of Israel and said to them, “Go and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1838AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1838AE\"></sup>take for yourselves lambs according to your families, and slay <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1838AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1838AF\"></sup>the Passover <i>lamb</i>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1839AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1839AG\"></sup>You shall take a bunch of hyssop and dip it in the blood which is in the basin, and apply some of the blood that is in the basin to the lintel and the two doorposts; and none of you shall go outside the door of his house until morning.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1840AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1840AH\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will pass through to smite the Egyptians; and when He sees the blood on the lintel and on the two doorposts, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will pass over the door and will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1840AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1840AI\"></sup>not allow the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1840AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1840AJ\"></sup>destroyer to come in to your houses to smite <i>you</i>.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1841AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1841AK\"></sup>you shall observe this event as an ordinance for you and your children forever.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>When you enter the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will give you, as He has promised, you shall observe this rite.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1843AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1843AL\"></sup>And when your children say to you, ‘What does this rite mean to you?’",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>you shall say, ‘It is a Passover sacrifice to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1844AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1844AM\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who passed over the houses of the sons of Israel in Egypt when He smote the Egyptians, but spared our homes.’” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1844AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1844AN\"></sup>And the people bowed low and worshiped.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then the sons of Israel went and did <i>so</i>; just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses and Aaron, so they did.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Now it came about at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1846AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1846AO\"></sup>midnight that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1846AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1846AP\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> struck all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1846AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1846AQ\"></sup>the firstborn in the land of Egypt, from the firstborn of Pharaoh who sat on his throne to the firstborn of the captive who was in the dungeon, and all the firstborn of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1846AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1846AR\"></sup>cattle.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Pharaoh arose in the night, he and all his servants and all the Egyptians, and there was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1847AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1847AS\"></sup>a great cry in Egypt, for there was no home where there was not someone dead.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1848AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1848AT\"></sup>he called for Moses and Aaron at night and said, “Rise up, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1848AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1848AU\"></sup>get out from among my people, both you and the sons of Israel; and go, worship the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as you have said.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1849AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1849AV\"></sup>both your flocks and your herds, as you have said, and go, and bless me also.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1850AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1850AW\"></sup>The Egyptians urged the people, to send them out of the land in haste, for they said, “We will all be dead.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>So the people took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1851AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1851AX\"></sup>their dough before it was leavened, <i>with</i> their kneading bowls bound up in the clothes on their shoulders.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1852AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1852AY\"></sup>Now the sons of Israel had done according to the word of Moses, for they had requested from the Egyptians articles of silver and articles of gold, and clothing;",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given the people favor in the sight of the Egyptians, so that they let them have their request. Thus they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1853AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1853AZ\"></sup>plundered the Egyptians.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Now the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1854BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1854BA\"></sup>sons of Israel journeyed from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1854BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1854BB\"></sup>Rameses to Succoth, about <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1854BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1854BC\"></sup>six hundred thousand men on foot, aside from children.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>A <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1855BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1855BD\"></sup>mixed multitude also went up with them, along with flocks and herds, a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1855BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1855BE\"></sup>very large number of livestock.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>They baked the dough which they had brought out of Egypt into cakes of unleavened bread. For it had not become leavened, since they were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1856BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1856BF\"></sup>driven out of Egypt and could not delay, nor had they prepared any provisions for themselves.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Now the time that the sons of Israel lived in Egypt was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1857BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1857BG\"></sup>four hundred and thirty years.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And at the end of four hundred and thirty years, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1858BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1858BH\"></sup>the very day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1858BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1858BI\"></sup>all the hosts of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> went out from the land of Egypt.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1859BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1859BJ\"></sup>It is a night to be observed for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for having brought them out from the land of Egypt; this night is for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to be observed by all the sons of Israel throughout their generations.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses and Aaron, “This is the ordinance of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1860BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1860BK\"></sup>the Passover: no <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1860BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1860BL\"></sup>foreigner is to eat of it;",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>but every man’s <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1861BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1861BM\"></sup>slave purchased with money, after you have circumcised him, then he may eat of it.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1862BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1862BN\"></sup>A sojourner or a hired servant shall not eat of it.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>It is to be eaten in a single house; you are not to bring forth any of the flesh outside of the house, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1863BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1863BO\"></sup>nor are you to break any bone of it.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1864BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1864BP\"></sup>All the congregation of Israel are to celebrate this.",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1865BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1865BQ\"></sup>if a stranger sojourns with you, and celebrates the Passover to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, let all his males be circumcised, and then let him come near to celebrate it; and he shall be like a native of the land. But no uncircumcised person may eat of it.",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1866BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1866BR\"></sup>The same law shall apply to the native as to the stranger who sojourns among you.”",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>Then all the sons of Israel did <i>so</i>; they did just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses and Aaron.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>And on that same day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1868BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1868BS\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought the sons of Israel out of the land of Egypt <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1868BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1868BT\"></sup>by their hosts."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1870A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1870A\"></sup>Sanctify to Me every firstborn, the first offspring of every womb among the sons of Israel, both of man and beast; it belongs to Me.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Moses said to the people, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1871B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1871B\"></sup>Remember this day in which you went out from Egypt, from the house of slavery; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1871C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1871C\"></sup>by a powerful hand the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought you out from this place. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1871D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1871D\"></sup>And nothing leavened shall be eaten.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>On this day in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1872E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1872E\"></sup>month of Abib, you are about to go forth.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>It shall be when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1873F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1873F\"></sup>brings you to the land of the Canaanite, the Hittite, the Amorite, the Hivite and the Jebusite, which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1873G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1873G\"></sup>He swore to your fathers to give you, a land flowing with milk and honey, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1873H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1873H\"></sup>that you shall observe this rite in this month.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1874I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1874I\"></sup>seven days you shall eat unleavened bread, and on the seventh day there shall be a feast to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Unleavened bread shall be eaten throughout the seven days; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1875J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1875J\"></sup>nothing leavened shall be seen among you, nor shall any leaven be seen among you in all your borders.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1876K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1876K\"></sup>You shall tell your son on that day, saying, ‘It is because of what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> did for me when I came out of Egypt.’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1877L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1877L\"></sup>it shall serve as a sign to you on your hand, and as a reminder on your forehead, that the law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> may be in your mouth; for with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1877M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1877M\"></sup>a powerful hand the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought you out of Egypt.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Therefore, you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1878N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1878N\"></sup>keep this ordinance at its appointed time from year to year.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Now when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1879O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1879O\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brings you to the land of the Canaanite, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1879P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1879P\"></sup>He swore to you and to your fathers, and gives it to you,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1880Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1880Q\"></sup>you shall devote to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the first offspring of every womb, and the first offspring of every beast that you own; the males belong to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1881R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1881R\"></sup>every first offspring of a donkey you shall redeem with a lamb, but if you do not redeem <i>it</i>, then you shall break its neck; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1881S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1881S\"></sup>every firstborn of man among your sons you shall redeem.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1882T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1882T\"></sup>And it shall be when your son asks you in time to come, saying, ‘What is this?’ then you shall say to him, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1882U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1882U\"></sup>With a powerful hand the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought us out of Egypt, from the house of slavery.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>It came about, when Pharaoh was stubborn about letting us go, that the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1883V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1883V\"></sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> killed every firstborn in the land of Egypt, both the firstborn of man and the firstborn of beast. Therefore, I sacrifice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> the males, the first offspring of every womb, but every firstborn of my sons I redeem.’",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1884W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1884W\"></sup>it shall serve as a sign on your hand and as phylacteries on your forehead, for with a powerful hand the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought us out of Egypt.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now when Pharaoh had let the people go, God did not lead them by the way of the land of the Philistines, even though it was near; for God said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1885X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1885X\"></sup>The people might change their minds when they see war, and return to Egypt.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Hence God led the people around by the way of the wilderness to the Red Sea; and the sons of Israel went up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1886Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1886Y\"></sup>in martial array from the land of Egypt.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Moses took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1887Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1887Z\"></sup>the bones of Joseph with him, for he had made the sons of Israel solemnly swear, saying, “God will surely take care of you, and you shall carry my bones from here with you.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then they set out from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1888AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1888AA\"></sup>Succoth and camped in Etham on the edge of the wilderness.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1889AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1889AB\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was going before them in a pillar of cloud by day to lead them on the way, and in a pillar of fire by night to give them light, that they might travel by day and by night.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1890AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1890AC\"></sup>did not take away the pillar of cloud by day, nor the pillar of fire by night, from before the people."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“Tell the sons of Israel to turn back and camp before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1892A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1892A\"></sup>Pi-hahiroth, between <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1892B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1892B\"></sup>Migdol and the sea; you shall camp in front of Baal-zephon, opposite it, by the sea.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>For Pharaoh will say of the sons of Israel, ‘They are wandering aimlessly in the land; the wilderness has shut them in.’",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1894C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1894C\"></sup>I will harden Pharaoh’s heart, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1894D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1894D\"></sup>he will chase after them; and I will be honored through Pharaoh and all his army, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1894E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1894E\"></sup>the Egyptians will know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” And they did so.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When the king of Egypt was told that the people had fled, Pharaoh and his servants had a change of heart toward the people, and they said, “What is this we have done, that we have let Israel go from serving us?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So he made his chariot ready and took his people with him;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and he took six hundred select chariots, and all the <i>other</i> chariots of Egypt with officers over all of them.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1898F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1898F\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> hardened the heart of Pharaoh, king of Egypt, and he chased after the sons of Israel as the sons of Israel were going out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1898G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1898G\"></sup>boldly.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1899H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1899H\"></sup>the Egyptians chased after them <i>with</i> all the horses <i>and</i> chariots of Pharaoh, his horsemen and his army, and they overtook them camping by the sea, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1899I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1899I\"></sup>beside Pi-hahiroth, in front of Baal-zephon.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>As Pharaoh drew near, the sons of Israel looked, and behold, the Egyptians were marching after them, and they became very frightened; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1900J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1900J\"></sup>so the sons of Israel cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1901K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1901K\"></sup>they said to Moses, “Is it because there were no graves in Egypt that you have taken us away to die in the wilderness? Why have you dealt with us in this way, bringing us out of Egypt?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1902L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1902L\"></sup>Is this not the word that we spoke to you in Egypt, saying, ‘Leave us alone that we may serve the Egyptians’? For it would have been better for us to serve the Egyptians than to die in the wilderness.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But Moses said to the people, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1903M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1903M\"></sup>Do not fear! Stand by and see <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1903N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1903N\"></sup>the salvation of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which He will accomplish for you today; for the Egyptians whom you have seen today, you will never see them again forever.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1904O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1904O\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will fight for you while <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1904P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1904P\"></sup>you keep silent.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Why are you crying out to Me? Tell the sons of Israel to go forward.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>As for you, lift up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1906Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1906Q\"></sup>your staff and stretch out your hand over the sea and divide it, and the sons of Israel shall go through the midst of the sea on dry land.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>As for Me, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1907R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1907R\"></sup>I will harden the hearts of the Egyptians so that they will go in after them; and I will be honored through Pharaoh and all his army, through his chariots and his horsemen.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1908S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1908S\"></sup>Then the Egyptians will know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, when I am honored through Pharaoh, through his chariots and his horsemen.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1909T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1909T\"></sup>The angel of God, who had been going before the camp of Israel, moved and went behind them; and the pillar of cloud moved from before them and stood behind them.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So it came between the camp of Egypt and the camp of Israel; and there was the cloud along with the darkness, yet it gave light at night. Thus the one did not come near the other all night.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1911U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1911U\"></sup>Then Moses stretched out his hand over the sea; and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> swept the sea <i>back</i> by a strong east wind all night and turned the sea into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1911V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1911V\"></sup>dry land, so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1911W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1911W\"></sup>the waters were divided.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1912X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1912X\"></sup>The sons of Israel went through the midst of the sea on the dry land, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1912Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1912Y\"></sup>the waters <i>were like</i> a wall to them on their right hand and on their left.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1913Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1913Z\"></sup>the Egyptians took up the pursuit, and all Pharaoh’s horses, his chariots and his horsemen went in after them into the midst of the sea.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>At the morning watch, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1914AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1914AA\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> looked down on the army of the Egyptians through the pillar of fire and cloud and brought the army of the Egyptians into confusion.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He caused their chariot wheels to swerve, and He made them drive with difficulty; so the Egyptians said, “Let us flee from Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1915AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1915AB\"></sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is fighting for them against the Egyptians.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1916AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1916AC\"></sup>Stretch out your hand over the sea so that the waters may come back over the Egyptians, over their chariots and their horsemen.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So Moses stretched out his hand over the sea, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1917AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1917AD\"></sup>the sea returned to its normal state at daybreak, while the Egyptians were fleeing right into it; then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1917AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1917AE\"></sup>overthrew the Egyptians in the midst of the sea.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The waters returned and covered the chariots and the horsemen, even Pharaoh’s entire army that had gone into the sea after them; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1918AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1918AF\"></sup>not even one of them remained.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>But the sons of Israel walked on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1919AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1919AG\"></sup>dry land through the midst of the sea, and the waters <i>were like</i> a wall to them on their right hand and on their left.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1920AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1920AH\"></sup>Thus the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> saved Israel that day from the hand of the Egyptians, and Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1920AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1920AI\"></sup>saw the Egyptians dead on the seashore.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>When Israel saw the great power which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had used against the Egyptians, the people feared the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1921AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1921AJ\"></sup>they believed in the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and in His servant Moses."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1922A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1922A\"></sup>Then Moses and the sons of Israel sang this song to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and said,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1922B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1922B\"></sup>I will sing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for He is highly exalted;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1922C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1922C\"></sup>The horse and its rider He has hurled into the sea.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1923D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1923D\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is my strength and song,And He has become my salvation;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1923E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1923E\"></sup>This is my God, and I will praise Him;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1923F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1923F\"></sup>My father’s God, and I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1923G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1923G\"></sup>extol Him.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1924H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1924H\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is a warrior;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1924I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1924I\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is His name.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1925J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1925J\"></sup>Pharaoh’s chariots and his army He has cast into the sea;And the choicest of his officers are drowned in the Red Sea.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“The deeps cover them;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1926K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1926K\"></sup>They went down into the depths like a stone.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1927L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1927L\"></sup>Your right hand, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, is majestic in power,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1927M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1927M\"></sup>Your right hand, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, shatters the enemy.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“And in the greatness of Your excellence You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1928N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1928N\"></sup>overthrow those who rise up against You;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1928O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1928O\"></sup>You send forth Your burning anger, <i>and</i> it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1928P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1928P\"></sup>consumes them as chaff.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1929Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1929Q\"></sup>At the blast of Your nostrils the waters were piled up,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1929R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1929R\"></sup>The flowing waters stood up like a heap;The deeps were congealed in the heart of the sea.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1930S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1930S\"></sup>The enemy said, ‘I will pursue, I will overtake, I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1930T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1930T\"></sup>divide the spoil;My desire shall be gratified against them;I will draw out my sword, my hand will destroy them.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1931U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1931U\"></sup>You blew with Your wind, the sea covered them;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1931V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1931V\"></sup>They sank like lead in the mighty waters.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1932W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1932W\"></sup>Who is like You among the gods, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?Who is like You, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1932X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1932X\"></sup>majestic in holiness,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1932Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1932Y\"></sup>Awesome in praises, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1932Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1932Z\"></sup>working wonders?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1933AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1933AA\"></sup>You stretched out Your right hand,The earth swallowed them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“In Your lovingkindness You have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1934AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1934AB\"></sup>led the people whom You have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1934AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1934AC\"></sup>redeemed;In Your strength You have guided <i>them</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1934AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1934AD\"></sup>to Your holy habitation.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1935AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1935AE\"></sup>The peoples have heard, they tremble;Anguish has gripped the inhabitants of Philistia.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“Then the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1936AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1936AF\"></sup>chiefs of Edom were dismayed;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1936AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1936AG\"></sup>The leaders of Moab, trembling grips them;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1936AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1936AH\"></sup>All the inhabitants of Canaan have melted away.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1937AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1937AI\"></sup>Terror and dread fall upon them;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1937AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1937AJ\"></sup>By the greatness of Your arm they are motionless as stone;Until Your people pass over, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,Until the people pass over whom You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1937AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1937AK\"></sup>have purchased.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1938AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1938AL\"></sup>You will bring them and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1938AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1938AM\"></sup>plant them in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1938AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1938AN\"></sup>the mountain of Your inheritance,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1938AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1938AO\"></sup>The place, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which You have made for Your dwelling,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1938AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1938AP\"></sup>The sanctuary, O Lord, which Your hands have established.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1939AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1939AQ\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shall reign forever and ever.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1940AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1940AR\"></sup>For the horses of Pharaoh with his chariots and his horsemen went into the sea, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought back the waters of the sea on them, but the sons of Israel walked on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1940AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1940AS\"></sup>dry land through the midst of the sea.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1941AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1941AT\"></sup>Miriam the prophetess, Aaron’s sister, took the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1941AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1941AU\"></sup>timbrel in her hand, and all the women went out after her with timbrels and with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1941AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1941AV\"></sup>dancing.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Miriam answered them,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1942AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1942AW\"></sup>Sing to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for He is highly exalted;The horse and his rider He has hurled into the sea.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1943AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1943AX\"></sup>Then Moses led Israel from the Red Sea, and they went out into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1943AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1943AY\"></sup>the wilderness of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1943AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1943AZ\"></sup>Shur; and they went three days in the wilderness and found no water.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When they came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1944BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1944BA\"></sup>Marah, they could not drink the waters of Marah, for they were bitter; therefore it was named Marah.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1945BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1945BB\"></sup>grumbled at Moses, saying, “What shall we drink?”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1946BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1946BC\"></sup>cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> showed him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1946BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1946BD\"></sup>a tree; and he threw <i>it</i> into the waters, and the waters became sweet.There He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1946BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1946BE\"></sup>made for them a statute and regulation, and there He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1946BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1946BF\"></sup>tested them.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And He said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1947BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1947BG\"></sup>If you will give earnest heed to the voice of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and do what is right in His sight, and give ear <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1947BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1947BH\"></sup>to His commandments, and keep all His statutes, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1947BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1947BI\"></sup>I will put none of the diseases on you which I have put on the Egyptians; for I, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1947BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1947BJ\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, am your healer.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then they came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1948BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1948BK\"></sup>Elim where there <i>were</i> twelve springs of water and seventy date palms, and they camped there beside the waters."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>Then they set out from Elim, and all the congregation of the sons of Israel came to the wilderness of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1949A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1949A\"></sup>Sin, which is between Elim and Sinai, on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1949B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1949B\"></sup>the fifteenth day of the second month after their departure from the land of Egypt.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The whole congregation of the sons of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1950C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1950C\"></sup>grumbled against Moses and Aaron in the wilderness.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The sons of Israel said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1951D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1951D\"></sup>Would that we had died by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> hand in the land of Egypt, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1951E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1951E\"></sup>when we sat by the pots of meat, when we ate bread to the full; for you have brought us out into this wilderness to kill this whole assembly with hunger.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1952F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1952F\"></sup>I will rain bread from heaven for you; and the people shall go out and gather a day’s portion every day, that I may <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1952G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1952G\"></sup>test them, whether or not they will walk in My instruction.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1953H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1953H\"></sup>On the sixth day, when they prepare what they bring in, it will be twice as much as they gather daily.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Moses and Aaron said to all the sons of Israel, “At evening <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1954I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1954I\"></sup>you will know that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has brought you out of the land of Egypt;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and in the morning you will see <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1955J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1955J\"></sup>the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1955K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1955K\"></sup>He hears your grumblings against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1955L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1955L\"></sup>what are we, that you grumble against us?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Moses said, “<i>This will happen</i> when the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> gives you meat to eat in the evening, and bread to the full in the morning; for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> hears your grumblings which you grumble against Him. And what are we? Your grumblings are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1956M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1956M\"></sup>not against us but against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Moses said to Aaron, “Say to all the congregation of the sons of Israel, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1957N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1957N\"></sup>Come near before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for He has heard your grumblings.’”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>It came about as Aaron spoke to the whole congregation of the sons of Israel, that they looked toward the wilderness, and behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1958O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1958O\"></sup>the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> appeared in the cloud.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1960P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1960P\"></sup>I have heard the grumblings of the sons of Israel; speak to them, saying, ‘At twilight you shall eat meat, and in the morning you shall be filled with bread; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1960Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1960Q\"></sup>you shall know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.’”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So it came about at evening that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1961R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1961R\"></sup>the quails came up and covered the camp, and in the morning <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1961S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1961S\"></sup>there was a layer of dew around the camp.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1962T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1962T\"></sup>When the layer of dew evaporated, behold, on the surface of the wilderness <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1962U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1962U\"></sup>there was a fine flake-like thing, fine as the frost on the ground.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When the sons of Israel saw <i>it</i>, they said to one another, “What is it?” For they did not know what it was. And Moses said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1963V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1963V\"></sup>It is the bread which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given you to eat.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded, ‘Gather of it every man as much as he should eat; you shall take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1964W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1964W\"></sup>an omer apiece according to the number of persons each of you has in his tent.’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The sons of Israel did so, and <i>some</i> gathered much and <i>some</i> little.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When they measured it with an omer, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1966X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1966X\"></sup>he who had gathered much had no excess, and he who had gathered little had no lack; every man gathered as much as he should eat.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Moses said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1967Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1967Y\"></sup>Let no man leave any of it until morning.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But they did not listen to Moses, and some left part of it until morning, and it bred worms and became foul; and Moses was angry with them.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They gathered it morning by morning, every man as much as he should eat; but when the sun grew hot, it would melt.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1970Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1970Z\"></sup>Now on the sixth day they gathered twice as much bread, two omers for each one. When all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1970AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1970AA\"></sup>leaders of the congregation came and told Moses,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>then he said to them, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> meant: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1971AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1971AB\"></sup>Tomorrow is a sabbath observance, a holy sabbath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Bake what you will bake and boil what you will boil, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1971AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1971AC\"></sup>all that is left over put aside to be kept until morning.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So they put it aside until morning, as Moses had ordered, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1972AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1972AD\"></sup>it did not become foul nor was there any worm in it.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Moses said, “Eat it today, for today is a sabbath to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; today you will not find it in the field.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1974AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1974AE\"></sup>Six days you shall gather it, but on the seventh day, <i>the</i> sabbath, there will be none.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>It came about on the seventh day that some of the people went out to gather, but they found none.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1976AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1976AF\"></sup>How long do you refuse to keep My commandments and My instructions?",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>See, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given you the sabbath; therefore He gives you bread for two days on the sixth day. Remain every man in his place; let no man go out of his place on the seventh day.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So the people rested on the seventh day.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The house of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1979AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1979AG\"></sup>Israel named it manna, and it was like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1979AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1979AH\"></sup>coriander seed, white, and its taste was like wafers with honey.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then Moses said, “This is what the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded, ‘Let an omerful of it be kept throughout your generations, that they may see the bread that I fed you in the wilderness, when I brought you out of the land of Egypt.’”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Moses said to Aaron, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1981AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1981AI\"></sup>Take a jar and put an omerful of manna in it, and place it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to be kept throughout your generations.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded Moses, so Aaron placed it before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1982AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1982AJ\"></sup>the Testimony, to be kept.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1983AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1983AK\"></sup>The sons of Israel ate the manna forty years, until they came to an inhabited land; they ate the manna until they came to the border of the land of Canaan.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>(Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1984AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1984AL\"></sup>an omer is a tenth of an ephah.)"
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>Then all the congregation of the sons of Israel journeyed by stages from the wilderness of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1985A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1985A\"></sup>Sin, according to the command of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and camped at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1985B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1985B\"></sup>Rephidim, and there was no water for the people to drink.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Therefore the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1986C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1986C\"></sup>quarreled with Moses and said, “Give us water that we may drink.” And Moses said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1986D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1986D\"></sup>Why do you quarrel with me? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1986E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1986E\"></sup>Why do you test the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But the people thirsted there for water; and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1987F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1987F\"></sup>grumbled against Moses and said, “Why, now, have you brought us up from Egypt, to kill us and our children and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1987G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1987G\"></sup>our livestock with thirst?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Moses cried out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, “What shall I do to this people? A <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1988H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1988H\"></sup>little more and they will stone me.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Pass before the people and take with you some of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1989I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1989I\"></sup>the elders of Israel; and take in your hand your staff with which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1989J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1989J\"></sup>you struck the Nile, and go.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Behold, I will stand before you there on the rock at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1990K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1990K\"></sup>Horeb; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1990L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1990L\"></sup>you shall strike the rock, and water will come out of it, that the people may drink.” And Moses did so in the sight of the elders of Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He named the place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1991M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1991M\"></sup>Massah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1991N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1991N\"></sup>Meribah because of the quarrel of the sons of Israel, and because they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1991O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1991O\"></sup>tested the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, “Is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> among us, or not?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1992P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1992P\"></sup>Amalek came and fought against Israel at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1992Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1992Q\"></sup>Rephidim.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So Moses said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1993R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1993R\"></sup>Joshua, “Choose men for us and go out, fight against Amalek. Tomorrow I will station myself on the top of the hill with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1993S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1993S\"></sup>the staff of God in my hand.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Joshua did as Moses told him, and fought against Amalek; and Moses, Aaron, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1994T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1994T\"></sup>Hur went up to the top of the hill.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So it came about when Moses held his hand up, that Israel prevailed, and when he let his hand down, Amalek prevailed.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But Moses’ hands were heavy. Then they took a stone and put it under him, and he sat on it; and Aaron and Hur <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1996U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1996U\"></sup>supported his hands, one on one side and one on the other. Thus his hands were steady until the sun set.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Joshua overwhelmed Amalek and his people with the edge of the sword.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1998V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1998V\"></sup>Write this in a book as a memorial and recite it to Joshua, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1998W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1998W\"></sup>I will utterly blot out the memory of Amalek from under heaven.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Moses built an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1999X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1999X\"></sup>altar and named it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-1999Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-1999Y\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is My Banner;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2000Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2000Z\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sworn; the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will have war against Amalek from generation to generation.”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2001A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2001A\"></sup>Jethro, the priest of Midian, Moses’ father-in-law, heard of all that God had done for Moses and for Israel His people, how the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had brought Israel out of Egypt.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Jethro, Moses’ father-in-law, took Moses’ wife <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2002B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2002B\"></sup>Zipporah, after he had sent her away,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and her <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2003C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2003C\"></sup>two sons, of whom one was named Gershom, for Moses said, “I have been <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2003D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2003D\"></sup>a sojourner in a foreign land.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The other was named <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2004E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2004E\"></sup>Eliezer, for <i>he said</i>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2004F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2004F\"></sup>The God of my father was my help, and delivered me from the sword of Pharaoh.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Jethro, Moses’ father-in-law, came with his sons and his wife to Moses in the wilderness where he was camped, at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2005G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2005G\"></sup>the mount of God.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He sent word to Moses, “I, your father-in-law Jethro, am coming to you with your wife and her two sons with her.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then Moses went out to meet his father-in-law, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2007H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2007H\"></sup>he bowed down and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2007I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2007I\"></sup>kissed him; and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2007J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2007J\"></sup>asked each other of their welfare and went into the tent.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Moses told his father-in-law all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had done to Pharaoh and to the Egyptians <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2008K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2008K\"></sup>for Israel’s sake, all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2008L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2008L\"></sup>hardship that had befallen them on the journey, and <i>how</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2008M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2008M\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had delivered them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Jethro rejoiced over all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2009N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2009N\"></sup>the goodness which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had done to Israel, in delivering them from the hand of the Egyptians.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So Jethro said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2010O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2010O\"></sup>Blessed be the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who delivered you from the hand of the Egyptians and from the hand of Pharaoh, <i>and</i> who delivered the people from under the hand of the Egyptians.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now I know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2011P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2011P\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is greater than all the gods; indeed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2011Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2011Q\"></sup>it was proven when they dealt proudly against the people.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2012R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2012R\"></sup>Then Jethro, Moses’ father-in-law, took a burnt offering and sacrifices for God, and Aaron came with all the elders of Israel to eat a meal with Moses’ father-in-law before God.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>It came about the next day that Moses sat to judge the people, and the people stood about Moses from the morning until the evening.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now when Moses’ father-in-law saw all that he was doing for the people, he said, “What is this thing that you are doing for the people? Why do you alone sit <i>as judge</i> and all the people stand about you from morning until evening?”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Moses said to his father-in-law, “Because the people come to me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2015S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2015S\"></sup>to inquire of God.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>When they have a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2016T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2016T\"></sup>dispute, it comes to me, and I judge between a man and his neighbor and make known the statutes of God and His laws.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Moses’ father-in-law said to him, “The thing that you are doing is not good.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2018U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2018U\"></sup>You will surely wear out, both yourself and these people who are with you, for the task is too heavy for you; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2018V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2018V\"></sup>you cannot do it alone.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Now listen to me: I will give you counsel, and God be with you. You be the people’s representative before God, and you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2019W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2019W\"></sup>bring the disputes to God,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2020X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2020X\"></sup>then teach them the statutes and the laws, and make known to them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2020Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2020Y\"></sup>the way in which they are to walk and the work they are to do.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Furthermore, you shall select out of all the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2021Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2021Z\"></sup>able men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2021AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2021AA\"></sup>who fear God, men of truth, those who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2021AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2021AB\"></sup>hate dishonest gain; and you shall place <i>these</i> over them <i>as</i> leaders of thousands, of hundreds, of fifties and of tens.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Let them judge the people at all times; and let it be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2022AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2022AC\"></sup>that every major dispute they will bring to you, but every minor dispute they themselves will judge. So it will be easier for you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2022AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2022AD\"></sup>they will bear <i>the burden</i> with you.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>If you do this thing and God <i>so</i> commands you, then you will be able to endure, and all these people also will go to their place in peace.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>So Moses listened to his father-in-law and did all that he had said.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Moses chose <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2025AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2025AE\"></sup>able men out of all Israel and made them heads over the people, leaders of thousands, of hundreds, of fifties and of tens.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>They judged the people at all times; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2026AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2026AF\"></sup>the difficult dispute they would bring to Moses, but every minor dispute they themselves would judge.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2027AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2027AG\"></sup>bade his father-in-law farewell, and he went his way into his own land."
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2028A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2028A\"></sup>In the third month after the sons of Israel had gone out of the land of Egypt, on that very day they came into the wilderness of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2028B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2028B\"></sup>Sinai.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>When they set out from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2029C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2029C\"></sup>Rephidim, they came to the wilderness of Sinai and camped in the wilderness; and there Israel camped in front of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2029D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2029D\"></sup>the mountain.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Moses went up to God, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2030E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2030E\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> called to him from the mountain, saying, “Thus you shall say to the house of Jacob and tell the sons of Israel:",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2031F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2031F\"></sup>You yourselves have seen what I did to the Egyptians, and <i>how</i> I bore you on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2031G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2031G\"></sup>eagles’ wings, and brought you to Myself.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now then, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2032H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2032H\"></sup>if you will indeed obey My voice and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2032I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2032I\"></sup>keep My covenant, then you shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2032J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2032J\"></sup>My own possession among all the peoples, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2032K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2032K\"></sup>all the earth is Mine;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and you shall be to Me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2033L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2033L\"></sup>a kingdom of priests and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2033M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2033M\"></sup>a holy nation.’ These are the words that you shall speak to the sons of Israel.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2034N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2034N\"></sup>So Moses came and called the elders of the people, and set before them all these words which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2035O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2035O\"></sup>All the people answered together and said, “All that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken we will do!” And Moses brought back the words of the people to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Behold, I will come to you in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2036P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2036P\"></sup>a thick cloud, so that the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2036Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2036Q\"></sup>people may hear when I speak with you and may also believe in you forever.” Then Moses told the words of the people to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> also said to Moses, “Go to the people and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2037R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2037R\"></sup>consecrate them today and tomorrow, and let them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2037S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2037S\"></sup>wash their garments;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and let them be ready for the third day, for on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2038T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2038T\"></sup>the third day the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will come down on Mount Sinai in the sight of all the people.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You shall set bounds for the people all around, saying, ‘Beware that you do not go up on the mountain or touch the border of it; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2039U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2039U\"></sup>whoever touches the mountain shall surely be put to death.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>No hand shall touch him, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2040V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2040V\"></sup>he shall surely be stoned or shot through; whether beast or man, he shall not live.’ When the ram’s horn sounds a long blast, they shall come up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2040W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2040W\"></sup>the mountain.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So Moses went down from the mountain to the people and consecrated the people, and they washed their garments.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He said to the people, “Be ready for the third day; do not go near a woman.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2043X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2043X\"></sup>So it came about on the third day, when it was morning, that there were thunder and lightning flashes and a thick cloud upon the mountain and a very loud trumpet sound, so that all the people who <i>were</i> in the camp trembled.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And Moses brought the people out of the camp to meet God, and they stood at the foot of the mountain.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2045Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2045Y\"></sup>Now Mount Sinai <i>was</i> all in smoke because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> descended upon it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2045Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2045Z\"></sup>in fire; and its smoke ascended like <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2045AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2045AA\"></sup>the smoke of a furnace, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2045AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2045AB\"></sup>the whole mountain quaked violently.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When the sound of the trumpet grew louder and louder, Moses spoke and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2046AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2046AC\"></sup>God answered him with thunder.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2047AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2047AD\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came down on Mount Sinai, to the top of the mountain; and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> called Moses to the top of the mountain, and Moses went up.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, “Go down, warn the people, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2048AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2048AE\"></sup>they do not break through to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to gaze, and many of them perish.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Also let the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2049AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2049AF\"></sup>priests who come near to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> consecrate themselves, or else the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will break out against them.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Moses said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “The people cannot come up to Mount Sinai, for You warned us, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2050AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2050AG\"></sup>Set bounds about the mountain and consecrate it.’”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Go down and come up <i>again</i>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2051AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2051AH\"></sup>you and Aaron with you; but do not let the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2051AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2051AI\"></sup>priests and the people break through to come up to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, or He will break forth upon them.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>So Moses went down to the people and told them."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>Then God spoke all these words, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2054A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2054A\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2054B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2054B\"></sup>who brought you out of the land of Egypt, out of the house of slavery.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2055C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2055C\"></sup>You shall have no other <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2055D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2055D\"></sup>gods before Me.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2056E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2056E\"></sup>You shall not make for yourself an idol, or any likeness of what is in heaven above or on the earth beneath or in the water under the earth.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2057F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2057F\"></sup>You shall not worship them or serve them; for I, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, am a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2057G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2057G\"></sup>jealous God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2057H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2057H\"></sup>visiting the iniquity of the fathers on the children, on the third and the fourth generations of those who hate Me,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>but showing lovingkindness to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2058I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2058I\"></sup>thousands, to those who love Me and keep My commandments.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2059J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2059J\"></sup>You shall not take the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God in vain, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will not leave him unpunished who takes His name in vain.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Remember <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2060K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2060K\"></sup>the sabbath day, to keep it holy.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2061L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2061L\"></sup>Six days you shall labor and do all your work,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>but the seventh day is a sabbath of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; <i>in it</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2062M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2062M\"></sup>you shall not do any work, you or your son or your daughter, your male or your female servant or your cattle or your sojourner who stays with you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2063N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2063N\"></sup>For in six days the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made the heavens and the earth, the sea and all that is in them, and rested on the seventh day; therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> blessed the sabbath day and made it holy.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2064O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2064O\"></sup>Honor your father and your mother, that your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2064P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2064P\"></sup>days may be prolonged in the land which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God gives you.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2065Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2065Q\"></sup>You shall not murder.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2066R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2066R\"></sup>You shall not commit adultery.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2067S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2067S\"></sup>You shall not steal.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2068T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2068T\"></sup>You shall not bear false witness against your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2068U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2068U\"></sup>neighbor.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2069V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2069V\"></sup>You shall not covet your neighbor’s house; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2069W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2069W\"></sup>you shall not covet your neighbor’s wife or his male servant or his female servant or his ox or his donkey or anything that belongs to your neighbor.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2070X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2070X\"></sup>All the people perceived the thunder and the lightning flashes and the sound of the trumpet and the mountain smoking; and when the people saw <i>it</i>, they trembled and stood at a distance.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2071Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2071Y\"></sup>Then they said to Moses, “Speak to us yourself and we will listen; but let not God speak to us, or we will die.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Moses said to the people, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2072Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2072Z\"></sup>Do not be afraid; for God has come in order <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2072AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2072AA\"></sup>to test you, and in order that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2072AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2072AB\"></sup>the fear of Him may remain with you, so that you may not sin.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So the people stood at a distance, while Moses approached <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2073AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2073AC\"></sup>the thick cloud where God <i>was</i>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Thus you shall say to the sons of Israel, ‘You yourselves have seen that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2074AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2074AD\"></sup>I have spoken to you from heaven.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2075AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2075AE\"></sup>You shall not make <i>other gods</i> besides Me; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2075AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2075AF\"></sup>gods of silver or gods of gold, you shall not make for yourselves.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>You shall make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2076AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2076AG\"></sup>an altar of earth for Me, and you shall sacrifice on it your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2076AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2076AH\"></sup>burnt offerings and your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2076AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2076AI\"></sup>peace offerings, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2076AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2076AJ\"></sup>your sheep and your oxen; in every place <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2076AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2076AK\"></sup>where I cause My name to be remembered, I will come to you and bless you.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>If you make an altar of stone for Me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2077AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2077AL\"></sup>you shall not build it of cut stones, for if you wield your tool on it, you will profane it.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And you shall not go up by steps to My altar, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2078AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2078AM\"></sup>your nakedness will not be exposed on it.’"
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>“Now these are the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2079A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2079A\"></sup>ordinances which you are to set before them:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“If you buy <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2080B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2080B\"></sup>a Hebrew slave, he shall serve for six years; but on the seventh he shall go out as a free man without payment.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>If he comes alone, he shall go out alone; if he is the husband of a wife, then his wife shall go out with him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>If his master gives him a wife, and she bears him sons or daughters, the wife and her children shall belong to her master, and he shall go out alone.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2083C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2083C\"></sup>if the slave plainly says, ‘I love my master, my wife and my children; I will not go out as a free man,’",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>then his master shall bring him to God, then he shall bring him to the door or the doorpost. And his master shall pierce his ear with an awl; and he shall serve him permanently.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2085D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2085D\"></sup>If a man sells his daughter as a female slave, she is not to go free <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2085E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2085E\"></sup>as the male slaves do.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>If she is displeasing in the eyes of her master who designated her for himself, then he shall let her be redeemed. He does not have authority to sell her to a foreign people because of his unfairness to her.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>If he designates her for his son, he shall deal with her according to the custom of daughters.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>If he takes to himself another woman, he may not reduce her food, her clothing, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2088F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2088F\"></sup>her conjugal rights.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>If he will not do these three <i>things</i> for her, then she shall go out for nothing, without <i>payment of</i> money.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2090G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2090G\"></sup>He who strikes a man so that he dies shall surely be put to death.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2091H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2091H\"></sup>But if he did not lie in wait <i>for him</i>, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2091I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2091I\"></sup>God let <i>him</i> fall into his hand, then I will appoint you a place to which he may flee.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2092J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2092J\"></sup>If, however, a man acts presumptuously toward his neighbor, so as to kill him craftily, you are to take him <i>even</i> from My altar, that he may die.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“He who strikes his father or his mother shall surely be put to death.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2094K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2094K\"></sup>He who kidnaps a man, whether he sells him or he is found in his possession, shall surely be put to death.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2095L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2095L\"></sup>He who curses his father or his mother shall surely be put to death.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“If men have a quarrel and one strikes the other with a stone or with <i>his</i> fist, and he does not die but remains in bed,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>if he gets up and walks around outside on his staff, then he who struck him shall go unpunished; he shall only pay for his loss of time, and shall take care of him until he is completely healed.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“If a man strikes his male or female slave with a rod and he dies at his hand, he shall be punished.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>If, however, he survives a day or two, no vengeance shall be taken; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2099M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2099M\"></sup>for he is his property.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“If men struggle with each other and strike a woman with child so that she gives birth prematurely, yet there is no injury, he shall surely be fined as the woman’s husband may demand of him, and he shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2100N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2100N\"></sup>pay as the judges <i>decide</i>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But if there is <i>any further</i> injury, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2101O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2101O\"></sup>then you shall appoint <i>as a penalty</i> life for life,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2102P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2102P\"></sup>eye for eye, tooth for tooth, hand for hand, foot for foot,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>burn for burn, wound for wound, bruise for bruise.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“If a man strikes the eye of his male or female slave, and destroys it, he shall let him go free on account of his eye.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And if he knocks out a tooth of his male or female slave, he shall let him go free on account of his tooth.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“If an ox gores a man or a woman to death, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2106Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2106Q\"></sup>the ox shall surely be stoned and its flesh shall not be eaten; but the owner of the ox shall go unpunished.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>If, however, an ox was previously in the habit of goring and its owner has been warned, yet he does not confine it and it kills a man or a woman, the ox shall be stoned and its owner also shall be put to death.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>If a ransom is demanded of him, then he shall give for the redemption of his life whatever is demanded of him.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Whether it gores a son or a daughter, it shall be done to him according to the same rule.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>If the ox gores a male or female slave, the owner shall give his <i>or her</i> master <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2110R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2110R\"></sup>thirty shekels of silver, and the ox shall be stoned.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“If a man opens a pit, or digs a pit and does not cover it over, and an ox or a donkey falls into it,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>the owner of the pit shall make restitution; he shall give money to its owner, and the dead <i>animal</i> shall become his.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>“If one man’s ox hurts another’s so that it dies, then they shall sell the live ox and divide its price equally; and also they shall divide the dead <i>ox</i>.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Or <i>if</i> it is known that the ox was previously in the habit of goring, yet its owner has not confined it, he shall surely pay ox for ox, and the dead <i>animal</i> shall become his."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span>“If a man steals an ox or a sheep and slaughters it or sells it, he shall pay five oxen for the ox and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2115A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2115A\"></sup>four sheep for the sheep.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“If the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2116B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2116B\"></sup>thief is caught while breaking in and is struck so that he dies, there will be no bloodguiltiness on his account.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><i>But</i> if the sun has risen on him, there will be bloodguiltiness on his account. He shall surely make restitution; if he owns nothing, then he shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2117C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2117C\"></sup>sold for his theft.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>If what he stole is actually found alive in his possession, whether an ox or a donkey or a sheep, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2118D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2118D\"></sup>he shall pay double.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“If a man lets a field or vineyard be grazed <i>bare</i> and lets his animal loose so that it grazes in another man’s field, he shall make restitution from the best of his own field and the best of his own vineyard.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“If a fire breaks out and spreads to thorn bushes, so that stacked grain or the standing grain or the field <i>itself</i> is consumed, he who started the fire shall surely make restitution.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2121E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2121E\"></sup>If a man gives his neighbor money or goods to keep <i>for him</i> and it is stolen from the man’s house, if the thief is caught, he shall pay double.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>If the thief is not caught, then the owner of the house shall appear before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2122F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2122F\"></sup>the judges, <i>to</i> determine whether he laid his hands on his neighbor’s property.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For every breach of trust, <i>whether it is</i> for ox, for donkey, for sheep, for clothing, <i>or</i> for any lost thing about which one says, ‘This is it,’ the case of both parties shall come before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2123G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2123G\"></sup>the judges; he whom the judges condemn shall pay double to his neighbor.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“If a man gives his neighbor a donkey, an ox, a sheep, or any animal to keep <i>for him</i>, and it dies or is hurt or is driven away while no one is looking,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2125H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2125H\"></sup>oath before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shall be made by the two of them that he has not laid hands on his neighbor’s property; and its owner shall accept <i>it</i>, and he shall not make restitution.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But if it is actually stolen from him, he shall make restitution to its owner.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>If it is all torn to pieces, let him bring it as evidence; he shall not make restitution for what has been torn to pieces.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“If a man borrows <i>anything</i> from his neighbor, and it is injured or dies while its owner is not with it, he shall make full restitution.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>If its owner is with it, he shall not make restitution; if it is hired, it came for its hire.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2130I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2130I\"></sup>If a man seduces a virgin who is not engaged, and lies with her, he must pay a dowry for her <i>to be</i> his wife.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>If her father absolutely refuses to give her to him, he shall pay money equal to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2131J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2131J\"></sup>dowry for virgins.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“You shall not allow a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2132K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2132K\"></sup>sorceress to live.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2133L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2133L\"></sup>Whoever lies with an animal shall surely be put to death.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2134M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2134M\"></sup>He who sacrifices to any god, other than to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> alone, shall be utterly destroyed.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2135N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2135N\"></sup>You shall not wrong a stranger or oppress him, for you were strangers in the land of Egypt.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2136O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2136O\"></sup>You shall not afflict any widow or orphan.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>If you afflict him at all, <i>and</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2137P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2137P\"></sup>if he does cry out to Me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2137Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2137Q\"></sup>I will surely hear his cry;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and My anger will be kindled, and I will kill you with the sword, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2138R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2138R\"></sup>and your wives shall become widows and your children fatherless.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2139S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2139S\"></sup>If you lend money to My people, to the poor among you, you are not to act as a creditor to him; you shall not charge him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2139T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2139T\"></sup>interest.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>If you ever take your neighbor’s cloak <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2140U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2140U\"></sup>as a pledge, you are to return it to him before the sun sets,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>for that is his only covering; it is his cloak for his body. What else shall he sleep in? And it shall come about that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2141V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2141V\"></sup>when he cries out to Me, I will hear <i>him</i>, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2141W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2141W\"></sup>I am gracious.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“You shall not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2142X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2142X\"></sup>curse God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2142Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2142Y\"></sup>nor curse a ruler of your people.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2143Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2143Z\"></sup>You shall not delay <i>the offering from</i> your harvest and your vintage. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2143AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2143AA\"></sup>The firstborn of your sons you shall give to Me.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2144AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2144AB\"></sup>You shall do the same with your oxen <i>and</i> with your sheep. It shall be with its mother seven days; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2144AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2144AC\"></sup>on the eighth day you shall give it to Me.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2145AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2145AD\"></sup>You shall be holy men to Me, therefore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2145AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2145AE\"></sup>you shall not eat <i>any</i> flesh torn to pieces in the field; you shall throw it to the dogs."
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2146A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2146A\"></sup>You shall not bear a false report; do not join your hand with a wicked man to be a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2146B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2146B\"></sup>malicious witness.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>You shall not follow the masses in doing evil, nor shall you testify in a dispute so as to turn aside after a multitude in order to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2147C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2147C\"></sup>pervert <i>justice</i>;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2148D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2148D\"></sup>nor shall you be partial to a poor man in his dispute.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2149E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2149E\"></sup>If you meet your enemy’s ox or his donkey wandering away, you shall surely return it to him.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2150F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2150F\"></sup>If you see the donkey of one who hates you lying <i>helpless</i> under its load, you shall refrain from leaving it to him, you shall surely release <i>it</i> with him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2151G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2151G\"></sup>You shall not pervert the justice <i>due</i> to your needy <i>brother</i> in his dispute.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2152H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2152H\"></sup>Keep far from a false charge, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2152I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2152I\"></sup>do not kill the innocent or the righteous, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2152J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2152J\"></sup>I will not acquit the guilty.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2153K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2153K\"></sup>You shall not take a bribe, for a bribe blinds the clear-sighted and subverts the cause of the just.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2154L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2154L\"></sup>You shall not oppress a stranger, since you yourselves know the feelings of a stranger, for you <i>also</i> were strangers in the land of Egypt.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2155M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2155M\"></sup>You shall sow your land for six years and gather in its yield,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>but <i>on</i> the seventh year you shall let it rest and lie fallow, so that the needy of your people may eat; and whatever they leave the beast of the field may eat. You are to do the same with your vineyard <i>and</i> your olive grove.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2157N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2157N\"></sup>Six days you are to do your work, but on the seventh day you shall cease <i>from labor</i> so that your ox and your donkey may rest, and the son of your female slave, as well as your stranger, may refresh themselves.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2158O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2158O\"></sup>concerning everything which I have said to you, be on your guard; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2158P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2158P\"></sup>do not mention the name of other gods, nor let <i>them</i> be heard from your mouth.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2159Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2159Q\"></sup>Three times a year you shall celebrate a feast to Me.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>You shall observe <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2160R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2160R\"></sup>the Feast of Unleavened Bread; for seven days you are to eat unleavened bread, as I commanded you, at the appointed time in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2160S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2160S\"></sup>month Abib, for in it you came out of Egypt. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2160T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2160T\"></sup>none shall appear before Me empty-handed.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Also <i>you shall observe</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2161U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2161U\"></sup>the Feast of the Harvest <i>of</i> the first fruits of your labors <i>from</i> what you sow in the field; also the Feast of the Ingathering at the end of the year <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2161V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2161V\"></sup>when you gather in <i>the fruit of</i> your labors from the field.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2162W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2162W\"></sup>Three times a year all your males shall appear before the Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2163X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2163X\"></sup>You shall not offer the blood of My sacrifice with leavened bread; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2163Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2163Y\"></sup>nor is the fat of My feast to remain overnight until morning.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“You shall bring <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2164Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2164Z\"></sup>the choice first fruits of your soil into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2164AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2164AA\"></sup>You are not to boil a young goat in the milk of its mother.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“Behold, I am going to send <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2165AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2165AB\"></sup>an angel before you to guard you along the way and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2165AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2165AC\"></sup>to bring you into the place which I have prepared.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Be on your guard before him and obey his voice; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2166AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2166AD\"></sup>do not be rebellious toward him, for he will not pardon your transgression, since <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2166AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2166AE\"></sup>My name is in him.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But if you truly obey his voice and do all that I say, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2167AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2167AF\"></sup>I will be an enemy to your enemies and an adversary to your adversaries.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2168AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2168AG\"></sup>For My angel will go before you and bring you in to <i>the land of</i> the Amorites, the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Canaanites, the Hivites and the Jebusites; and I will completely destroy them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2169AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2169AH\"></sup>You shall not worship their gods, nor serve them, nor do according to their deeds; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2169AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2169AI\"></sup>but you shall utterly overthrow them and break their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2169AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2169AJ\"></sup><i>sacred</i> pillars in pieces.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2170AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2170AK\"></sup>But you shall serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, and He will bless your bread and your water; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2170AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2170AL\"></sup>I will remove sickness from your midst.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>There shall be no one miscarrying or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2171AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2171AM\"></sup>barren in your land; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2171AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2171AN\"></sup>I will fulfill the number of your days.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2172AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2172AO\"></sup>send My terror ahead of you, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2172AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2172AP\"></sup>throw into confusion all the people among whom you come, and I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2172AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2172AQ\"></sup>make all your enemies turn <i>their</i> backs to you.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>I will send <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2173AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2173AR\"></sup>hornets ahead of you so that they will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2173AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2173AS\"></sup>drive out the Hivites, the Canaanites, and the Hittites before you.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2174AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2174AT\"></sup>I will not drive them out before you in a single year, that the land may not become desolate and the beasts of the field become too numerous for you.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>I will drive them out before you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2175AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2175AU\"></sup>little by little, until you become fruitful and take possession of the land.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2176AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2176AV\"></sup>I will fix your boundary from the Red Sea to the sea of the Philistines, and from the wilderness to the River <i>Euphrates</i>; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2176AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2176AW\"></sup>for I will deliver the inhabitants of the land into your hand, and you will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2176AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2176AX\"></sup>drive them out before you.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2177AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2177AY\"></sup>You shall make no covenant with them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2177AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2177AZ\"></sup>or with their gods.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2178BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2178BA\"></sup>They shall not live in your land, because they will make you sin against Me; for <i>if</i> you serve their gods, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2178BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2178BB\"></sup>it will surely be a snare to you.”"
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span>Then He said to Moses, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2179A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2179A\"></sup>Come up to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you and Aaron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2179B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2179B\"></sup>Nadab and Abihu and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2179C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2179C\"></sup>seventy of the elders of Israel, and you shall worship at a distance.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Moses alone, however, shall come near to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but they shall not come near, nor shall the people come up with him.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Moses came and recounted to the people all the words of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and all the ordinances; and all the people answered with one voice and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2181D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2181D\"></sup>All the words which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken we will do!”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2182E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2182E\"></sup>Moses wrote down all the words of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. Then he arose early in the morning, and built an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2182F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2182F\"></sup>altar at the foot of the mountain with twelve pillars for the twelve tribes of Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He sent young men of the sons of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2183G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2183G\"></sup>and they offered burnt offerings and sacrificed young bulls as peace offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2184H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2184H\"></sup>Moses took half of the blood and put <i>it</i> in basins, and the <i>other</i> half of the blood he sprinkled on the altar.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then he took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2185I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2185I\"></sup>the book of the covenant and read <i>it</i> in the hearing of the people; and they said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2185J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2185J\"></sup>All that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken we will do, and we will be obedient!”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2186K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2186K\"></sup>Moses took the blood and sprinkled <i>it</i> on the people, and said, “Behold <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2186L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2186L\"></sup>the blood of the covenant, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has made with you in accordance with all these words.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then Moses went up with Aaron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2187M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2187M\"></sup>Nadab and Abihu, and seventy of the elders of Israel,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2188N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2188N\"></sup>they saw the God of Israel; and under His feet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2188O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2188O\"></sup>there appeared to be a pavement of sapphire, as clear as the sky itself.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Yet He did not stretch out His hand against the nobles of the sons of Israel; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2189P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2189P\"></sup>they saw God, and they ate and drank.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Come up to Me on the mountain and remain there, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2190Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2190Q\"></sup>I will give you the stone tablets with the law and the commandment which I have written for their instruction.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Moses arose with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2191R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2191R\"></sup>Joshua his servant, and Moses went up to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2191S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2191S\"></sup>the mountain of God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But to the elders he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2192T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2192T\"></sup>Wait here for us until we return to you. And behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2192U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2192U\"></sup>Aaron and Hur are with you; whoever has a legal matter, let him approach them.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Moses went up to the mountain, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2193V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2193V\"></sup>the cloud covered the mountain.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2194W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2194W\"></sup>The glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> rested on Mount Sinai, and the cloud covered it for six days; and on the seventh day He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2194X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2194X\"></sup>called to Moses from the midst of the cloud.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2195Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2195Y\"></sup>And to the eyes of the sons of Israel the appearance of the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was like a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2195Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2195Z\"></sup>consuming fire on the mountain top.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Moses entered the midst of the cloud as he went up to the mountain; and Moses was on the mountain <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2196AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2196AA\"></sup>forty days and forty nights."
		},
		"25": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">25 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2198A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2198A\"></sup>Tell the sons of Israel to raise a contribution for Me; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2198B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2198B\"></sup>from every man whose heart moves him you shall raise My contribution.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>This is the contribution which you are to raise from them: gold, silver and bronze,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2200C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2200C\"></sup>blue, purple and scarlet <i>material</i>, fine linen, goat <i>hair</i>,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>rams’ skins dyed red, porpoise skins, acacia wood,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2202D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2202D\"></sup>oil for lighting, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2202E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2202E\"></sup>spices for the anointing oil and for the fragrant incense,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>onyx stones and setting stones for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2203F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2203F\"></sup>ephod and for the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2203G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2203G\"></sup>breastpiece.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Let them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2204H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2204H\"></sup>construct a sanctuary for Me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2204I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2204I\"></sup>that I may dwell among them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2205J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2205J\"></sup>According to all that I am going to show you, <i>as</i> the pattern of the tabernacle and the pattern of all its furniture, just so you shall construct <i>it</i>.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2206K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2206K\"></sup>They shall construct an ark of acacia wood two and a half cubits long, and one and a half cubits wide, and one and a half cubits high.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2207L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2207L\"></sup>overlay it with pure gold, inside and out you shall overlay it, and you shall make a gold molding around it.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You shall cast four gold rings for it and fasten them on its four feet, and two rings shall be on one side of it and two rings on the other side of it.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You shall make poles of acacia wood and overlay them with gold.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You shall put the poles into the rings on the sides of the ark, to carry the ark with them.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2211M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2211M\"></sup>poles shall remain in the rings of the ark; they shall not be removed from it.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>You shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2212N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2212N\"></sup>put into the ark the testimony which I shall give you.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“You shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2213O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2213O\"></sup>make a mercy seat of pure gold, two and a half cubits long and one and a half cubits wide.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>You shall make two cherubim of gold, make them of hammered work at the two ends of the mercy seat.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Make one cherub at one end and one cherub at the other end; you shall make the cherubim <i>of one piece</i> with the mercy seat at its two ends.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2216P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2216P\"></sup>The cherubim shall have <i>their</i> wings spread upward, covering the mercy seat with their wings and facing one another; the faces of the cherubim are to be <i>turned</i> toward the mercy seat.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2217Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2217Q\"></sup>You shall put the mercy seat on top of the ark, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2217R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2217R\"></sup>in the ark you shall put the testimony which I will give to you.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2218S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2218S\"></sup>There I will meet with you; and from above the mercy seat, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2218T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2218T\"></sup>between the two cherubim which are upon the ark of the testimony, I will speak to you about all that I will give you in commandment for the sons of Israel.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2219U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2219U\"></sup>You shall make a table of acacia wood, two cubits long and one cubit wide and one and a half cubits high.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>You shall overlay it with pure gold and make a gold <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2220V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2220V\"></sup>border around it.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>You shall make for it a rim of a handbreadth around <i>it</i>; and you shall make a gold border for the rim around it.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>You shall make four gold rings for it and put rings on the four corners which are on its four feet.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The rings shall be close to the rim as holders for the poles to carry the table.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>You shall make the poles of acacia wood and overlay them with gold, so that with them the table may be carried.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>You shall make its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2225W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2225W\"></sup>dishes and its pans and its jars and its bowls with which to pour drink offerings; you shall make them of pure gold.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>You shall set <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2226X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2226X\"></sup>the bread of the Presence on the table before Me at all times.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2227Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2227Y\"></sup>Then you shall make a lampstand of pure gold. The lampstand <i>and</i> its base and its shaft are to be made of hammered work; its cups, its bulbs and its flowers shall be <i>of one piece</i> with it.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2228Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2228Z\"></sup>Six branches shall go out from its sides; three branches of the lampstand from its one side and three branches of the lampstand from its other side.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2229AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2229AA\"></sup>Three cups <i>shall be</i> shaped like almond <i>blossoms</i> in the one branch, a bulb and a flower, and three cups shaped like almond <i>blossoms</i> in the other branch, a bulb and a flower—so for six branches going out from the lampstand;",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2230AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2230AB\"></sup>in the lampstand four cups shaped like almond <i>blossoms</i>, its bulbs and its flowers.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2231AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2231AC\"></sup>A bulb shall be under the <i>first</i> pair of branches <i>coming</i> out of it, and a bulb under the <i>second</i> pair of branches <i>coming</i> out of it, and a bulb under the <i>third</i> pair of branches <i>coming</i> out of it, for the six branches coming out of the lampstand.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2232AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2232AD\"></sup>Their bulbs and their branches <i>shall be of one piece</i> with it; all of it shall be one piece of hammered work of pure gold.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Then you shall make its lamps seven <i>in number</i>; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2233AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2233AE\"></sup>they shall mount its lamps so as to shed light on the space in front of it.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Its snuffers and their trays <i>shall be</i> of pure gold.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>It shall be made from a talent of pure gold, with all these utensils.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2236AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2236AF\"></sup>See that you make <i>them</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2236AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2236AG\"></sup>after the pattern for them, which was shown to you on the mountain."
		},
		"26": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">26 </span>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2237A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2237A\"></sup>Moreover you shall make the tabernacle with ten curtains of fine twisted linen and blue and purple and scarlet <i>material</i>; you shall make them with cherubim, the work of a skillful workman.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The length of each curtain shall be twenty-eight cubits, and the width of each curtain four cubits; all the curtains shall have the same measurements.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Five curtains shall be joined to one another, and <i>the other</i> five curtains <i>shall be</i> joined to one another.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You shall make loops of blue on the edge of the outermost curtain in the <i>first</i> set, and likewise you shall make <i>them</i> on the edge of the curtain that is outermost in the second set.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You shall make fifty loops in the one curtain, and you shall make fifty loops on the edge of the curtain that is in the second set; the loops shall be opposite each other.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You shall make fifty clasps of gold, and join the curtains to one another with the clasps so that the tabernacle will be a unit.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2243B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2243B\"></sup>you shall make curtains of goats’ <i>hair</i> for a tent over the tabernacle; you shall make eleven curtains in all.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The length of each curtain <i>shall be</i> thirty cubits, and the width of each curtain four cubits; the eleven curtains shall have the same measurements.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You shall join five curtains by themselves and the <i>other</i> six curtains by themselves, and you shall double over the sixth curtain at the front of the tent.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You shall make fifty loops on the edge of the curtain that is outermost in the <i>first</i> set, and fifty loops on the edge of the curtain <i>that is outermost in</i> the second set.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“You shall make fifty clasps of bronze, and you shall put the clasps into the loops and join the tent together so that it will be a unit.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The overlapping part that is left over in the curtains of the tent, the half curtain that is left over, shall lap over the back of the tabernacle.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The cubit on one side and the cubit on the other, of what is left over in the length of the curtains of the tent, shall lap over the sides of the tabernacle on one side and on the other, to cover it.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2250C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2250C\"></sup>You shall make a covering for the tent of rams’ skins dyed red and a covering of porpoise skins above.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“Then you shall make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2251D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2251D\"></sup>the boards for the tabernacle of acacia wood, standing upright.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Ten cubits <i>shall be</i> the length of each board and one and a half cubits the width of each board.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><i>There shall be</i> two tenons for each board, fitted to one another; thus you shall do for all the boards of the tabernacle.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>You shall make the boards for the tabernacle: twenty boards for the south side.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>You shall make forty <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2255E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2255E\"></sup>sockets of silver under the twenty boards, two sockets under one board for its two tenons and two sockets under another board for its two tenons;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and for the second side of the tabernacle, on the north side, twenty boards,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and their forty sockets of silver; two sockets under one board and two sockets under another board.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For the rear of the tabernacle, to the west, you shall make six boards.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>You shall make two boards for the corners of the tabernacle at the rear.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>They shall be double beneath, and together they shall be complete to its top to the first ring; thus it shall be with both of them: they shall form the two corners.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>There shall be eight boards with their sockets of silver, sixteen sockets; two sockets under one board and two sockets under another board.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“Then you shall make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2262F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2262F\"></sup>bars of acacia wood, five for the boards of one side of the tabernacle,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and five bars for the boards of the other side of the tabernacle, and five bars for the boards of the side of the tabernacle for the rear <i>side</i> to the west.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The middle bar in the center of the boards shall pass through from end to end.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>You shall overlay the boards with gold and make their rings of gold <i>as</i> holders for the bars; and you shall overlay the bars with gold.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then you shall erect the tabernacle <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2266G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2266G\"></sup>according to its plan which you have been shown in the mountain.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“You shall make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2267H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2267H\"></sup>a veil of blue and purple and scarlet <i>material</i> and fine twisted linen; it shall be made with cherubim, the work of a skillful workman.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>You shall hang it on four pillars of acacia overlaid with gold, their hooks <i>also being of</i> gold, on four sockets of silver.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>You shall hang up the veil under the clasps, and shall bring in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2269I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2269I\"></sup>the ark of the testimony there within the veil; and the veil shall serve for you as a partition <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2269J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2269J\"></sup>between the holy place and the holy of holies.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2270K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2270K\"></sup>You shall put the mercy seat on the ark of the testimony in the holy of holies.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2271L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2271L\"></sup>You shall set the table outside the veil, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2271M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2271M\"></sup>lampstand opposite the table on the side of the tabernacle toward the south; and you shall put the table on the north side.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2272N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2272N\"></sup>You shall make a screen for the doorway of the tent of blue and purple and scarlet <i>material</i> and fine twisted linen, the work of a weaver.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2273O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2273O\"></sup>You shall make five pillars of acacia for the screen and overlay them with gold, their hooks <i>also being of</i> gold; and you shall cast five sockets of bronze for them."
		},
		"27": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">27 </span>“And you shall make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2274A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2274A\"></sup>the altar of acacia wood, five cubits long and five cubits wide; the altar shall be square, and its height shall be three cubits.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>You shall make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2275B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2275B\"></sup>its horns on its four corners; its horns shall be of one piece with it, and you shall overlay it with bronze.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You shall make its pails for removing its ashes, and its shovels and its basins and its forks and its firepans; you shall make all its utensils of bronze.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You shall make for it a grating of network of bronze, and on the net you shall make four bronze rings at its four corners.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You shall put it beneath, under the ledge of the altar, so that the net will reach halfway up the altar.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You shall make poles for the altar, poles of acacia wood, and overlay them with bronze.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Its poles shall be inserted into the rings, so that the poles shall be on the two sides of the altar <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2280C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2280C\"></sup>when it is carried.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You shall make it hollow with planks; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2281D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2281D\"></sup>as it was shown to you in the mountain, so they shall make <i>it</i>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“You shall make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2282E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2282E\"></sup>the court of the tabernacle. On the south side <i>there shall be</i> hangings for the court of fine twisted linen one hundred cubits long for one side;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and its pillars <i>shall be</i> twenty, with their twenty sockets of bronze; the hooks of the pillars and their bands <i>shall be</i> of silver.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Likewise for the north side in length <i>there shall be</i> hangings one hundred <i>cubits</i> long, and its twenty pillars with their twenty sockets of bronze; the hooks of the pillars and their bands <i>shall be</i> of silver.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><i>For</i> the width of the court on the west side <i>shall be</i> hangings of fifty cubits <i>with</i> their ten pillars and their ten sockets.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The width of the court on the east side <i>shall be</i> fifty cubits.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The hangings for the <i>one</i> side <i>of the gate shall be</i> fifteen cubits <i>with</i> their three pillars and their three sockets.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And for the other side <i>shall be</i> hangings of fifteen cubits <i>with</i> their three pillars and their three sockets.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For the gate of the court <i>there shall be</i> a screen of twenty cubits, of blue and purple and scarlet <i>material</i> and fine twisted linen, the work of a weaver, <i>with</i> their four pillars and their four sockets.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>All the pillars around the court shall be furnished with silver bands <i>with</i> their hooks of silver and their sockets of bronze.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The length of the court <i>shall be</i> one hundred cubits, and the width fifty throughout, and the height five cubits of fine twisted linen, and their sockets of bronze.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>All the utensils of the tabernacle <i>used</i> in all its service, and all its pegs, and all the pegs of the court, <i>shall be</i> of bronze.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“You shall charge the sons of Israel, that they bring you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2293F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2293F\"></sup>clear oil of beaten olives for the light, to make a lamp burn continually.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>In the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2294G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2294G\"></sup>tent of meeting, outside <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2294H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2294H\"></sup>the veil which is before the testimony, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2294I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2294I\"></sup>Aaron and his sons shall keep it in order from evening to morning before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; <i>it shall be</i> a perpetual <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2294J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2294J\"></sup>statute throughout their generations for the sons of Israel."
		},
		"28": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">28 </span>“Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2295A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2295A\"></sup>bring near to yourself Aaron your brother, and his sons with him, from among the sons of Israel, to minister as priest to Me—Aaron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2295B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2295B\"></sup>Nadab and Abihu, Eleazar and Ithamar, Aaron’s sons.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>You shall make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2296C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2296C\"></sup>holy garments for Aaron your brother, for glory and for beauty.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You shall speak to all the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2297D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2297D\"></sup>skillful persons <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2297E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2297E\"></sup>whom I have endowed with the spirit of wisdom, that they make Aaron’s garments to consecrate him, that he may minister as priest to Me.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>These are the garments which they shall make: a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2298F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2298F\"></sup>breastpiece and an ephod and a robe and a tunic of checkered work, a turban and a sash, and they shall make holy garments for Aaron your brother and his sons, that he may minister as priest to Me.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They shall take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2299G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2299G\"></sup>the gold and the blue and the purple and the scarlet <i>material</i> and the fine linen.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“They shall also make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2300H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2300H\"></sup>the ephod of gold, of blue and purple <i>and</i> scarlet <i>material</i> and fine twisted linen, the work of the skillful workman.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>It shall have two shoulder pieces joined to its two ends, that it may be joined.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The skillfully woven band, which is on it, shall be like its workmanship, of the same material: of gold, of blue and purple and scarlet <i>material</i> and fine twisted linen.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You shall take two onyx stones and engrave on them the names of the sons of Israel,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>six of their names on the one stone and the names of the remaining six on the other stone, according to their birth.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>As a jeweler engraves a signet, you shall engrave the two stones according to the names of the sons of Israel; you shall set them in filigree <i>settings</i> of gold.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You shall put the two stones on the shoulder pieces of the ephod, <i>as</i> stones of memorial for the sons of Israel, and Aaron shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2306I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2306I\"></sup>bear their names before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on his two shoulders <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2306J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2306J\"></sup>for a memorial.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2307K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2307K\"></sup>You shall make filigree <i>settings</i> of gold,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and two chains of pure gold; you shall make them of twisted cordage work, and you shall put the corded chains on the filigree <i>settings</i>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2309L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2309L\"></sup>You shall make a breastpiece of judgment, the work of a skillful workman; like the work of the ephod you shall make it: of gold, of blue and purple and scarlet <i>material</i> and fine twisted linen you shall make it.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>It shall be square <i>and</i> folded double, a span in length and a span in width.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>You shall mount on it four rows of stones; the first row <i>shall be</i> a row of ruby, topaz and emerald;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and the second row a turquoise, a sapphire and a diamond;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and the third row a jacinth, an agate and an amethyst;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and the fourth row a beryl and an onyx and a jasper; they shall be set in gold filigree.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The stones shall be according to the names of the sons of Israel: twelve, according to their names; they shall be <i>like</i> the engravings of a seal, each <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2315M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2315M\"></sup>according to his name for the twelve tribes.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>You shall make on the breastpiece chains of twisted cordage work in pure gold.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>You shall make on the breastpiece two rings of gold, and shall put the two rings on the two ends of the breastpiece.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>You shall put the two cords of gold on the two rings at the ends of the breastpiece.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>You shall put the <i>other</i> two ends of the two cords on the two filigree <i>settings</i>, and put them on the shoulder pieces of the ephod, at the front of it.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>You shall make two rings of gold and shall place them on the two ends of the breastpiece, on the edge of it, which is toward the inner side of the ephod.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>You shall make two rings of gold and put them on the bottom of the two shoulder pieces of the ephod, on the front of it close to the place where it is joined, above the skillfully woven band of the ephod.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>They shall bind the breastpiece by its rings to the rings of the ephod with a blue cord, so that it will be on the skillfully woven band of the ephod, and that the breastpiece will not come loose from the ephod.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Aaron shall carry the names of the sons of Israel in the breastpiece of judgment over his heart when he enters the holy place, for a memorial before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> continually.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2324N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2324N\"></sup>You shall put in the breastpiece of judgment the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2324O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2324O\"></sup>Urim and the Thummim, and they shall be over Aaron’s heart when he goes in before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and Aaron shall carry the judgment of the sons of Israel over his heart before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> continually.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2325P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2325P\"></sup>You shall make the robe of the ephod all of blue.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>There shall be an opening at its top in the middle of it; around its opening there shall be a binding of woven work, like the opening of a coat of mail, so that it will not be torn.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>You shall make on its hem pomegranates of blue and purple and scarlet <i>material</i>, all around on its hem, and bells of gold between them all around:",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>a golden bell and a pomegranate, a golden bell and a pomegranate, all around on the hem of the robe.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>It shall be on Aaron when he ministers; and its tinkling shall be heard when he enters and leaves the holy place before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, so that he will not die.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“You shall also make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2330Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2330Q\"></sup>a plate of pure gold and shall engrave on it, like the engravings of a seal, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2330R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2330R\"></sup>Holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>You shall fasten it on a blue cord, and it shall be on the turban; it shall be at the front of the turban.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>It shall be on Aaron’s forehead, and Aaron shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2332S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2332S\"></sup>take away the iniquity of the holy things which the sons of Israel consecrate, with regard to all their holy gifts; and it shall always be on his forehead, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2332T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2332T\"></sup>they may be accepted before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“You shall weave <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2333U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2333U\"></sup>the tunic of checkered work of fine linen, and shall make a turban of fine linen, and you shall make a sash, the work of a weaver.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>“For Aaron’s sons you shall make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2334V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2334V\"></sup>tunics; you shall also make sashes for them, and you shall make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2334W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2334W\"></sup>caps for them, for glory and for beauty.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>You shall put them on Aaron your brother and on his sons with him; and you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2335X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2335X\"></sup>anoint them and ordain them and consecrate them, that they may serve Me as priests.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>You shall make for them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2336Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2336Y\"></sup>linen breeches to cover <i>their</i> bare flesh; they shall reach from the loins even to the thighs.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>They shall be on Aaron and on his sons when they enter the tent of meeting, or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2337Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2337Z\"></sup>when they approach the altar to minister in the holy place, so that they do not incur guilt and die. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2337AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2337AA\"></sup>It <i>shall be</i> a statute forever to him and to his descendants after him."
		},
		"29": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">29 </span>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2338A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2338A\"></sup>Now this is what you shall do to them to consecrate them to minister as priests to Me: take one young bull and two rams without blemish,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2339B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2339B\"></sup>unleavened bread and unleavened cakes mixed with oil, and unleavened wafers spread with oil; you shall make them of fine wheat flour.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You shall put them in one basket, and present them in the basket along with the bull and the two rams.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2341C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2341C\"></sup>you shall bring Aaron and his sons to the doorway of the tent of meeting and wash them with water.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You shall take the garments, and put on Aaron the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2342D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2342D\"></sup>tunic and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2342E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2342E\"></sup>the robe of the ephod and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2342F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2342F\"></sup>the ephod and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2342G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2342G\"></sup>the breastpiece, and gird him with the skillfully <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2342H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2342H\"></sup>woven band of the ephod;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and you shall set the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2343I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2343I\"></sup>turban on his head and put <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2343J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2343J\"></sup>the holy crown on the turban.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then you shall take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2344K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2344K\"></sup>the anointing oil and pour it on his head and anoint him.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You shall bring his sons and put <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2345L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2345L\"></sup>tunics on them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You shall gird them with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2346M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2346M\"></sup>sashes, Aaron and his sons, and bind caps on them, and they shall have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2346N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2346N\"></sup>the priesthood by a perpetual statute. So you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2346O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2346O\"></sup>ordain Aaron and his sons.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“Then you shall bring the bull before the tent of meeting, and Aaron and his sons shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2347P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2347P\"></sup>lay their hands on the head of the bull.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You shall slaughter the bull before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at the doorway of the tent of meeting.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2349Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2349Q\"></sup>take some of the blood of the bull and put <i>it</i> on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2349R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2349R\"></sup>the horns of the altar with your finger; and you shall pour out all the blood at the base of the altar.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>You shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2350S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2350S\"></sup>take all the fat that covers the entrails and the lobe of the liver, and the two kidneys and the fat that is on them, and offer them up in smoke on the altar.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2351T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2351T\"></sup>the flesh of the bull and its hide and its refuse, you shall burn with fire outside the camp; it is a sin offering.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2352U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2352U\"></sup>You shall also take the one ram, and Aaron and his sons shall lay their hands on the head of the ram;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and you shall slaughter the ram and shall take its blood and sprinkle it around on the altar.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then you shall cut the ram into its pieces, and wash its entrails and its legs, and put <i>them</i> with its pieces and its head.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>You shall offer up in smoke the whole ram on the altar; it is a burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2355V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2355V\"></sup>it is a soothing aroma, an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2356W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2356W\"></sup>you shall take the other ram, and Aaron and his sons shall lay their hands on the head of the ram.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You shall slaughter the ram, and take some of its blood and put <i>it</i> on the lobe of Aaron’s right ear and on the lobes of his sons’ right ears and on the thumbs of their right hands and on the big toes of their right feet, and sprinkle the <i>rest of the</i> blood around on the altar.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then you shall take some of the blood that is on the altar and some of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2358X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2358X\"></sup>anointing oil, and sprinkle <i>it</i> on Aaron and on his garments and on his sons and on his sons’ garments with him; so he and his garments shall be consecrated, as well as his sons and his sons’ garments with him.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“You shall also take the fat from the ram and the fat tail, and the fat that covers the entrails and the lobe of the liver, and the two kidneys and the fat that is on them and the right thigh (for it is a ram of ordination),",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>and one cake of bread and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2360Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2360Y\"></sup>one cake of bread <i>mixed with</i> oil and one wafer from the basket of unleavened bread which is <i>set</i> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and you shall put all these in the hands of Aaron and in the hands of his sons, and shall wave them as a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2362Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2362Z\"></sup>You shall take them from their hands, and offer them up in smoke on the altar on the burnt offering for a soothing aroma before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; it is an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“Then you shall take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2363AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2363AA\"></sup>the breast of Aaron’s ram of ordination, and wave it as a wave offering before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and it shall be your portion.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>You shall consecrate the breast of the wave offering and the thigh of the heave offering which was waved and which was offered from the ram of ordination, from the one which was for Aaron and from the one which was for his sons.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>It shall be for Aaron and his sons as <i>their</i> portion forever from the sons of Israel, for it is a heave offering; and it shall be a heave offering from the sons of Israel from the sacrifices of their peace offerings, <i>even</i> their heave offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2366AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2366AB\"></sup>The holy garments of Aaron shall be for his sons after him, that in them they may be anointed and ordained.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>For seven days the one of his sons who is priest in his stead shall put them on when he enters the tent of meeting to minister in the holy place.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“You shall take the ram of ordination and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2368AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2368AC\"></sup>boil its flesh in a holy place.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Aaron and his sons shall eat the flesh of the ram and the bread that is in the basket, at the doorway of the tent of meeting.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2370AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2370AD\"></sup>they shall eat those things by which atonement was made at their ordination <i>and</i> consecration; but a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2370AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2370AE\"></sup>layman shall not eat <i>them</i>, because they are holy.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2371AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2371AF\"></sup>If any of the flesh of ordination or any of the bread remains until morning, then you shall burn the remainder with fire; it shall not be eaten, because it is holy.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>“Thus you shall do to Aaron and to his sons, according to all that I have commanded you; you shall ordain them through <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2372AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2372AG\"></sup>seven days.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2373AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2373AH\"></sup>Each day you shall offer a bull as a sin offering for atonement, and you shall purify the altar when you make atonement for it, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2373AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2373AI\"></sup>you shall anoint it to consecrate it.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>For seven days you shall make atonement for the altar and consecrate it; then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2374AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2374AJ\"></sup>the altar shall be most holy, <i>and</i> whatever touches the altar shall be holy.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>“Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2375AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2375AK\"></sup>this is what you shall offer on the altar: two one year old lambs each day, continuously.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2376AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2376AL\"></sup>one lamb you shall offer in the morning and the other lamb you shall offer at twilight;",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>and there <i>shall be</i> one-tenth <i>of an ephah</i> of fine flour mixed with one-fourth of a hin of beaten oil, and one-fourth of a hin of wine for a drink offering with one lamb.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>The other lamb you shall offer at twilight, and shall offer with it the same grain offering and the same drink offering as in the morning, for a soothing aroma, an offering by fire to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>It shall be a continual burnt offering throughout your generations at the doorway of the tent of meeting before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2379AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2379AM\"></sup>where I will meet with you, to speak to you there.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>I will meet there with the sons of Israel, and it shall be consecrated by My glory.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>I will consecrate the tent of meeting and the altar; I will also consecrate Aaron and his sons to minister as priests to Me.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2382AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2382AN\"></sup>I will dwell among the sons of Israel and will be their God.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>They shall know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2383AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2383AO\"></sup>I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God who brought them out of the land of Egypt, that I might dwell among them; I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God."
		},
		"30": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">30 </span>“Moreover, you shall make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2384A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2384A\"></sup>an altar as a place for burning incense; you shall make it of acacia wood.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Its length <i>shall be</i> a cubit, and its width a cubit, it shall be square, and its height <i>shall be</i> two cubits; its horns <i>shall be</i> of one piece with it.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>You shall overlay it with pure gold, its top and its sides all around, and its horns; and you shall make a gold molding all around for it.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You shall make two gold rings for it under its molding; you shall make <i>them</i> on its two side walls—on opposite sides—and they shall be holders for poles with which to carry it.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>You shall make the poles of acacia wood and overlay them with gold.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You shall put this altar in front of the veil that is near the ark of the testimony, in front of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2389B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2389B\"></sup>mercy seat that is over <i>the ark of</i> the testimony, where I will meet with you.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Aaron shall burn fragrant incense on it; he shall burn it every morning when he trims the lamps.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When Aaron trims the lamps at twilight, he shall burn incense. <i>There shall be</i> perpetual incense before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> throughout your generations.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>You shall not offer any strange incense on this altar, or burnt offering or meal offering; and you shall not pour out a drink offering on it.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Aaron shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2393C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2393C\"></sup>make atonement on its horns once a year; he shall make atonement on it with the blood of the sin offering of atonement once a year throughout your generations. It is most holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> also spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“When you take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2395D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2395D\"></sup>a census of the sons of Israel to number them, then each one of them shall give <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2395E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2395E\"></sup>a ransom for himself to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, when you number them, so that there will be no plague among them when you number them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>This is what everyone who is numbered shall give: half a shekel according to the shekel of the sanctuary (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2396F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2396F\"></sup>the shekel is twenty gerahs), half a shekel as a contribution to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Everyone who is numbered, from twenty years old and over, shall give the contribution to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The rich shall not pay more and the poor shall not pay less than the half shekel, when you give the contribution to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to make atonement for yourselves.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>You shall take the atonement money from the sons of Israel and shall give it for the service of the tent of meeting, that it may be a memorial for the sons of Israel before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, to make atonement for yourselves.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“You shall also make <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2401G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2401G\"></sup>a laver of bronze, with its base of bronze, for washing; and you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2401H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2401H\"></sup>put it between the tent of meeting and the altar, and you shall put water in it.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Aaron and his sons shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2402I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2402I\"></sup>wash their hands and their feet from it;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>when they enter the tent of meeting, they shall wash with water, so that they will not die; or when they approach the altar to minister, by offering up in smoke a fire <i>sacrifice</i> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So they shall wash their hands and their feet, so that they will not die; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2404J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2404J\"></sup>it shall be a perpetual statute for them, for Aaron and his descendants throughout their generations.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Moreover, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Take also for yourself the finest of spices: of flowing myrrh five hundred <i>shekels</i>, and of fragrant cinnamon half as much, two hundred and fifty, and of fragrant cane two hundred and fifty,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and of cassia five hundred, according to the shekel of the sanctuary, and of olive oil a hin.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>You shall make of these a holy anointing oil, a perfume mixture, the work of a perfumer; it shall be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2408K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2408K\"></sup>a holy anointing oil.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>With it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2409L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2409L\"></sup>you shall anoint the tent of meeting and the ark of the testimony,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and the table and all its utensils, and the lampstand and its utensils, and the altar of incense,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and the altar of burnt offering and all its utensils, and the laver and its stand.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>You shall also consecrate them, that they may be most holy; whatever touches them shall be holy.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2413M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2413M\"></sup>You shall anoint Aaron and his sons, and consecrate them, that they may minister as priests to Me.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>You shall speak to the sons of Israel, saying, ‘This shall be a holy anointing oil to Me throughout your generations.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>It shall not be poured on anyone’s body, nor shall you make <i>any</i> like it in the same proportions; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2415N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2415N\"></sup>it is holy, <i>and</i> it shall be holy to you.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2416O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2416O\"></sup>Whoever shall mix <i>any</i> like it or whoever puts any of it on a layman <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2416P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2416P\"></sup>shall be cut off from his people.’”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Take for yourself spices, stacte and onycha and galbanum, spices with pure frankincense; there shall be an equal part of each.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>With it you shall make incense, a perfume, the work of a perfumer, salted, pure, <i>and</i> holy.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>You shall beat some of it very fine, and put part of it before the testimony in the tent of meeting <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2419Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2419Q\"></sup>where I will meet with you; it shall be most holy to you.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>The incense which you shall make, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2420R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2420R\"></sup>you shall not make in the same proportions for yourselves; it shall be holy to you for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2421S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2421S\"></sup>Whoever shall make <i>any</i> like it, to use as perfume, shall be cut off from his people.”"
		},
		"31": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">31 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2422A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2422A\"></sup>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“See, I have called by name Bezalel, the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2423B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2423B\"></sup>son of Uri, the son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2424C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2424C\"></sup>filled him with the Spirit of God in wisdom, in understanding, in knowledge, and in all <i>kinds of</i> craftsmanship,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>to make artistic designs for work in gold, in silver, and in bronze,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and in the cutting of stones for settings, and in the carving of wood, that he may work in all <i>kinds of</i> craftsmanship.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And behold, I Myself have appointed with him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2427D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2427D\"></sup>Oholiab, the son of Ahisamach, of the tribe of Dan; and in the hearts of all who are skillful I have put skill, that they may make all that I have commanded you:",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2428E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2428E\"></sup>the tent of meeting, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2428F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2428F\"></sup>the ark of testimony, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2428G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2428G\"></sup>the mercy seat upon it, and all the furniture of the tent,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2429H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2429H\"></sup>the table also and its utensils, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2429I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2429I\"></sup>pure <i>gold</i> lampstand with all its utensils, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2429J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2429J\"></sup>the altar of incense,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2430K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2430K\"></sup>the altar of burnt offering also with all its utensils, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2430L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2430L\"></sup>the laver and its stand,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2431M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2431M\"></sup>woven garments as well, and the holy garments for Aaron the priest, and the garments of his sons, <i>with which</i> to carry on their priesthood;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2432N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2432N\"></sup>the anointing oil also, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2432O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2432O\"></sup>fragrant incense for the holy place, they are to make <i>them</i> according to all that I have commanded you.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“But as for you, speak to the sons of Israel, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2434P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2434P\"></sup>You shall surely observe My sabbaths; for <i>this</i> is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2434Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2434Q\"></sup>a sign between Me and you throughout your generations, that you may know that I am the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> who sanctifies you.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Therefore you are to observe the sabbath, for it is holy to you. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2435R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2435R\"></sup>Everyone who profanes it shall surely be put to death; for whoever does any work on it, that person shall be cut off from among his people.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2436S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2436S\"></sup>For six days work may be done, but on the seventh day there is a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2436T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2436T\"></sup>sabbath of complete rest, holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2436U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2436U\"></sup>whoever does any work on the sabbath day shall surely be put to death.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So the sons of Israel shall observe the sabbath, to celebrate the sabbath throughout their generations as a perpetual covenant.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2438V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2438V\"></sup>It is a sign between Me and the sons of Israel forever; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2438W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2438W\"></sup>for in six days the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> made heaven and earth, but on the seventh day He ceased <i>from labor</i>, and was refreshed.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When He had finished speaking with him upon Mount Sinai, He gave Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2439X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2439X\"></sup>the two tablets of the testimony, tablets of stone, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2439Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2439Y\"></sup>written by the finger of God."
		},
		"32": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">32 </span>Now when the people saw that Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2440A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2440A\"></sup>delayed to come down from the mountain, the people assembled about Aaron and said to him, “Come, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2440B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2440B\"></sup>make us a god who will go before us; as for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2440C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2440C\"></sup>this Moses, the man who brought us up from the land of Egypt, we do not know what has become of him.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Aaron said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2441D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2441D\"></sup>Tear off the gold rings which are in the ears of your wives, your sons, and your daughters, and bring <i>them</i> to me.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then all the people tore off the gold rings which were in their ears and brought <i>them</i> to Aaron.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He took <i>this</i> from their hand, and fashioned it with a graving tool and made it into a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2443E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2443E\"></sup>molten calf; and they said, “This is your god, O Israel, who brought you up from the land of Egypt.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now when Aaron saw <i>this</i>, he built an altar before it; and Aaron made a proclamation and said, “Tomorrow <i>shall be</i> a feast to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So the next day they rose early and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2445F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2445F\"></sup>offered burnt offerings, and brought peace offerings; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2445G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2445G\"></sup>the people sat down to eat and to drink, and rose up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2445H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2445H\"></sup>to play.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, “Go down at once, for your people, whom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2446I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2446I\"></sup>you brought up from the land of Egypt, have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2446J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2446J\"></sup>corrupted <i>themselves</i>.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They have quickly turned aside from the way which I commanded them. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2447K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2447K\"></sup>They have made for themselves a molten calf, and have worshiped it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2447L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2447L\"></sup>have sacrificed to it and said, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2447M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2447M\"></sup>This is your god, O Israel, who brought you up from the land of Egypt!’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2448N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2448N\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “I have seen this people, and behold, they are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2448O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2448O\"></sup>an obstinate people.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2449P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2449P\"></sup>let Me alone, that My anger may burn against them and that I may destroy them; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2449Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2449Q\"></sup>I will make of you a great nation.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2450R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2450R\"></sup>Moses entreated the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God, and said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, why does Your anger burn against Your people whom You have brought out from the land of Egypt with great power and with a mighty hand?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Why should <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2451S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2451S\"></sup>the Egyptians speak, saying, ‘With evil <i>intent</i> He brought them out to kill them in the mountains and to destroy them from the face of the earth’? Turn from Your burning anger and change Your mind about <i>doing</i> harm to Your people.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Remember Abraham, Isaac, and Israel, Your servants to whom You <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2452T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2452T\"></sup>swore by Yourself, and said to them, ‘I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2452U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2452U\"></sup>multiply your descendants as the stars of the heavens, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2452V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2452V\"></sup>all this land of which I have spoken I will give to your descendants, and they shall inherit <i>it</i> forever.’”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2453W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2453W\"></sup>So the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> changed His mind about the harm which He said He would do to His people.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2454X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2454X\"></sup>Then Moses turned and went down from the mountain with the two tablets of the testimony in his hand, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2454Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2454Y\"></sup>tablets which were written on both sides; they were written on one <i>side</i> and the other.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The tablets were God’s work, and the writing was God’s writing engraved on the tablets.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now when Joshua heard the sound of the people as they shouted, he said to Moses, “There is a sound of war in the camp.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But he said,“It is not the sound of the cry of triumph,Nor is it the sound of the cry of defeat;But the sound of singing I hear.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>It came about, as soon as Moses came near the camp, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2458Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2458Z\"></sup>he saw the calf and <i>the</i> dancing; and Moses’ anger burned, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2458AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2458AA\"></sup>he threw the tablets from his hands and shattered them at the foot of the mountain.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2459AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2459AB\"></sup>He took the calf which they had made and burned <i>it</i> with fire, and ground it to powder, and scattered it over the surface of the water and made the sons of Israel drink <i>it</i>.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Moses said to Aaron, “What did this people do to you, that you have brought <i>such</i> great sin upon them?”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Aaron said, “Do not let the anger of my lord burn; you know the people yourself, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2461AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2461AC\"></sup>that they are prone to evil.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2462AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2462AD\"></sup>they said to me, ‘Make a god for us who will go before us; for this Moses, the man who brought us up from the land of Egypt, we do not know what has become of him.’",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>I said to them, ‘Whoever has any gold, let them tear it off.’ So they gave <i>it</i> to me, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2463AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2463AE\"></sup>I threw it into the fire, and out came this calf.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now when Moses saw that the people were out of control—for Aaron had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2464AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2464AF\"></sup>let them get out of control to be a derision among their enemies—",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>then Moses stood in the gate of the camp, and said, “Whoever is for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <i>come</i> to me!” And all the sons of Levi gathered together to him.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He said to them, “Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, ‘Every man <i>of you</i> put his sword upon his thigh, and go back and forth from gate to gate in the camp, and kill every man his brother, and every man his friend, and every man his neighbor.’”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2467AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2467AG\"></sup>the sons of Levi did as Moses instructed, and about three thousand men of the people fell that day.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Moses said, “Dedicate yourselves today to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>—for every man has been against his son and against his brother—in order that He may bestow a blessing upon you today.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>On the next day Moses said to the people, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2469AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2469AH\"></sup>You yourselves have committed a great sin; and now I am going up to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, perhaps I can <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2469AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2469AI\"></sup>make atonement for your sin.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then Moses returned to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and said, “Alas, this people has committed a great sin, and they have made a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2470AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2470AJ\"></sup>god of gold for themselves.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>But now, if You will, forgive their sin—and if not, please blot me out from Your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2471AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2471AK\"></sup>book which You have written!”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Whoever has sinned against Me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2472AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2472AL\"></sup>I will blot him out of My book.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But go now, lead the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2473AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2473AM\"></sup>where I told you. Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2473AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2473AN\"></sup>My angel shall go before you; nevertheless <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2473AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2473AO\"></sup>in the day when I punish, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2473AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2473AP\"></sup>I will punish them for their sin.”",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2474AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2474AQ\"></sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> smote the people, because of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2474AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2474AR\"></sup>what they did with the calf which Aaron had made."
		},
		"33": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">33 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, “Depart, go up from here, you and the people whom you have brought up from the land of Egypt, to the land of which <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2475A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2475A\"></sup>I swore to Abraham, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2475B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2475B\"></sup>Isaac, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2475C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2475C\"></sup>Jacob, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2475D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2475D\"></sup>To your descendants I will give it.’",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I will send <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2476E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2476E\"></sup>an angel before you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2476F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2476F\"></sup>I will drive out the Canaanite, the Amorite, the Hittite, the Perizzite, the Hivite and the Jebusite.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><i>Go up</i> to a land <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2477G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2477G\"></sup>flowing with milk and honey; for I will not go up in your midst, because you are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2477H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2477H\"></sup>an obstinate people, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2477I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2477I\"></sup>I might destroy you on the way.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>When the people heard this sad word, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2478J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2478J\"></sup>they went into mourning, and none of them put on his ornaments.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had said to Moses, “Say to the sons of Israel, ‘You are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2479K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2479K\"></sup>an obstinate people; should I go up in your midst for one moment, I would destroy you. Now therefore, put off your ornaments from you, that I may know what I shall do with you.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So the sons of Israel stripped themselves of their ornaments, from Mount Horeb <i>onward</i>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now Moses used to take <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2481L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2481L\"></sup>the tent and pitch it outside the camp, a good distance from the camp, and he called it the tent of meeting. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2481M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2481M\"></sup>everyone who sought the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> would go out to the tent of meeting which was outside the camp.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And it came about, whenever Moses went out to the tent, that all the people would arise and stand, each at the entrance of his tent, and gaze after Moses until he entered the tent.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Whenever Moses entered the tent, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2483N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2483N\"></sup>the pillar of cloud would descend and stand at the entrance of the tent; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2483O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2483O\"></sup>and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> would speak with Moses.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When all the people saw the pillar of cloud standing at the entrance of the tent, all the people would arise and worship, each at the entrance of his tent.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Thus <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2485P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2485P\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> used to speak to Moses face to face, just as a man speaks to his friend. When Moses returned to the camp, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2485Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2485Q\"></sup>his servant Joshua, the son of Nun, a young man, would not depart from the tent.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Moses said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “See, You say to me, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2486R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2486R\"></sup>Bring up this people!’ But You Yourself have not let me know <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2486S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2486S\"></sup>whom You will send with me. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2486T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2486T\"></sup>Moreover, You have said, ‘I have known you by name, and you have also found favor in My sight.’",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now therefore, I pray You, if I have found favor in Your sight, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2487U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2487U\"></sup>let me know Your ways that I may know You, so that I may find favor in Your sight. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2487V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2487V\"></sup>Consider too, that this nation is Your people.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And He said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2488W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2488W\"></sup>My presence shall go <i>with you</i>, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2488X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2488X\"></sup>I will give you rest.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then he said to Him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2489Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2489Y\"></sup>If Your presence does not go <i>with us</i>, do not lead us up from here.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For how then can it be known that I have found favor in Your sight, I and Your people? Is it not by Your going with us, so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2490Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2490Z\"></sup>we, I and Your people, may be distinguished from all the <i>other</i> people who are upon the face of the earth?”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “I will also do this thing of which you have spoken; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2491AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2491AA\"></sup>for you have found favor in My sight and I have known you by name.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2492AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2492AB\"></sup>Then Moses said, “I pray You, show me Your glory!”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And He said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2493AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2493AC\"></sup>I Myself will make all My goodness pass before you, and will proclaim the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> before you; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2493AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2493AD\"></sup>I will be gracious to whom I will be gracious, and will show compassion on whom I will show compassion.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But He said, “You cannot see My face, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2494AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2494AE\"></sup>for no man can see Me and live!”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “Behold, there is a place by Me, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2495AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2495AF\"></sup>you shall stand <i>there</i> on the rock;",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>and it will come about, while My glory is passing by, that I will put you in the cleft of the rock and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2496AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2496AG\"></sup>cover you with My hand until I have passed by.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Then I will take My hand away and you shall see My back, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2497AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2497AH\"></sup>My face shall not be seen.”"
		},
		"34": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">34 </span>Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “Cut out for yourself <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2498A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2498A\"></sup>two stone tablets like the former ones, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2498B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2498B\"></sup>I will write on the tablets the words that were on the former tablets which you shattered.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So be ready by morning, and come up in the morning to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2499C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2499C\"></sup>Mount Sinai, and present yourself there to Me on the top of the mountain.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2500D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2500D\"></sup>No man is to come up with you, nor let any man be seen anywhere on the mountain; even the flocks and the herds may not graze in front of that mountain.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So he cut out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2501E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2501E\"></sup>two stone tablets like the former ones, and Moses rose up early in the morning and went up to Mount Sinai, as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded him, and he took two stone tablets in his hand.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2502F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2502F\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> descended in the cloud and stood there with him as he called upon the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> passed by in front of him and proclaimed, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2503G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2503G\"></sup>compassionate and gracious, slow to anger, and abounding in lovingkindness and truth;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2504H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2504H\"></sup>keeps lovingkindness for thousands, who forgives iniquity, transgression and sin; yet He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2504I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2504I\"></sup>will by no means leave <i>the guilty</i> unpunished, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2504J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2504J\"></sup>visiting the iniquity of fathers on the children and on the grandchildren to the third and fourth generations.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Moses made haste <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2505K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2505K\"></sup>to bow low toward the earth and worship.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2506L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2506L\"></sup>If now I have found favor in Your sight, O Lord, I pray, let the Lord go along in our midst, even though <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2506M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2506M\"></sup>the people are so obstinate, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2506N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2506N\"></sup>pardon our iniquity and our sin, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2506O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2506O\"></sup>take us as Your own possession.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then God said, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2507P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2507P\"></sup>I am going to make a covenant. Before all your people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2507Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2507Q\"></sup>I will perform miracles which have not been produced in all the earth nor among any of the nations; and all the people among whom you live will see the working of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, for it is a fearful thing that I am going to perform with you.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“Be sure to observe what I am commanding you this day: behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2508R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2508R\"></sup>I am going to drive out the Amorite before you, and the Canaanite, the Hittite, the Perizzite, the Hivite and the Jebusite.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2509S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2509S\"></sup>Watch yourself that you make no covenant with the inhabitants of the land into which you are going, or it will become a snare in your midst.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2510T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2510T\"></sup>But <i>rather</i>, you are to tear down their altars and smash their <i>sacred</i> pillars and cut down their <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2510U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2510U\"></sup>Asherim",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>—for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2511V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2511V\"></sup>you shall not worship any other god, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, whose name is Jealous, is a jealous God—",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>otherwise you might make a covenant with the inhabitants of the land and they would play the harlot with their gods and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2512W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2512W\"></sup>sacrifice to their gods, and someone <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2512X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2512X\"></sup>might invite you to eat of his sacrifice,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2513Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2513Y\"></sup>you might take some of his daughters for your sons, and his daughters might play the harlot with their gods and cause your sons <i>also</i> to play the harlot with their gods.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2514Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2514Z\"></sup>You shall make for yourself no molten gods.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“You shall observe <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2515AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2515AA\"></sup>the Feast of Unleavened Bread. For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2515AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2515AB\"></sup>seven days you are to eat unleavened bread, as I commanded you, at the appointed time in the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2515AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2515AC\"></sup>month of Abib, for in the month of Abib you came out of Egypt.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2516AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2516AD\"></sup>The first offspring from every womb belongs to Me, and all your male livestock, the first offspring from cattle and sheep.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2517AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2517AE\"></sup>You shall redeem with a lamb the first offspring from a donkey; and if you do not redeem <i>it</i>, then you shall break its neck. You shall redeem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2517AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2517AF\"></sup>all the firstborn of your sons. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2517AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2517AG\"></sup>None shall appear before Me empty-handed.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“You shall work <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2518AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2518AH\"></sup>six days, but on the seventh day you shall rest; <i>even</i> during plowing time and harvest you shall rest.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>You shall celebrate <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2519AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2519AI\"></sup>the Feast of Weeks, <i>that is</i>, the first fruits of the wheat harvest, and the Feast of Ingathering at the turn of the year.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2520AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2520AJ\"></sup>Three times a year all your males are to appear before the Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>, the God of Israel.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For I will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2521AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2521AK\"></sup>drive out nations before you and enlarge your borders, and no man shall covet your land when you go up three times a year to appear before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2522AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2522AL\"></sup>You shall not offer the blood of My sacrifice with leavened bread, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2522AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2522AM\"></sup>nor is the sacrifice of the Feast of the Passover to be left over until morning.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“You shall bring <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2523AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2523AN\"></sup>the very first of the first fruits of your soil into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God.“You shall not boil a young goat in its mother’s milk.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to Moses, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2524AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2524AO\"></sup>Write down these words, for in accordance with these words I have made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2524AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2524AP\"></sup>a covenant with you and with Israel.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So he was there with the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2525AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2525AQ\"></sup>forty days and forty nights; he did not eat bread or drink water. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2525AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2525AR\"></sup>he wrote on the tablets the words of the covenant, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2525AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2525AS\"></sup>the Ten Commandments.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>It came about when Moses was coming down from Mount Sinai (and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2526AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2526AT\"></sup>two tablets of the testimony <i>were</i> in Moses’ hand as he was coming down from the mountain), that Moses did not know that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2526AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2526AU\"></sup>the skin of his face shone because of his speaking with Him.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So when Aaron and all the sons of Israel saw Moses, behold, the skin of his face shone, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2527AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2527AV\"></sup>they were afraid to come near him.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then Moses called to them, and Aaron and all the rulers in the congregation returned to him; and Moses spoke to them.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Afterward all the sons of Israel came near, and he commanded them <i>to do</i> everything that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had spoken to him on Mount Sinai.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>When Moses had finished speaking with them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2530AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2530AW\"></sup>he put a veil over his face.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But whenever Moses went in before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to speak with Him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2531AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2531AX\"></sup>he would take off the veil until he came out; and whenever he came out and spoke to the sons of Israel what he had been commanded,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2532AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2532AY\"></sup>the sons of Israel would see the face of Moses, that the skin of Moses’ face shone. So Moses would replace the veil over his face until he went in to speak with Him."
		},
		"35": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">35 </span>Then Moses assembled all the congregation of the sons of Israel, and said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2533A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2533A\"></sup>These are the things that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded <i>you</i> to do:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2534B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2534B\"></sup>For six days work may be done, but on the seventh day you shall have a holy <i>day</i>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2534C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2534C\"></sup>a sabbath of complete rest to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2534D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2534D\"></sup>whoever does any work on it shall be put to death.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2535E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2535E\"></sup>You shall not kindle a fire in any of your dwellings on the sabbath day.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Moses spoke to all the congregation of the sons of Israel, saying, “This is the thing which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded, saying,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2537F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2537F\"></sup>Take from among you a contribution to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; whoever is of a willing heart, let him bring it as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> contribution: gold, silver, and bronze,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and blue, purple and scarlet <i>material</i>, fine linen, goats’ <i>hair</i>,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and rams’ skins dyed red, and porpoise skins, and acacia wood,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and oil for lighting, and spices for the anointing oil, and for the fragrant incense,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and onyx stones and setting stones for the ephod and for the breastpiece.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2542G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2542G\"></sup>Let every skillful man among you come, and make all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded:",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2543H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2543H\"></sup>tabernacle, its tent and its covering, its hooks and its boards, its bars, its pillars, and its sockets;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2544I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2544I\"></sup>ark and its poles, the mercy seat, and the curtain of the screen;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2545J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2545J\"></sup>table and its poles, and all its utensils, and the bread of the Presence;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2546K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2546K\"></sup>lampstand also for the light and its utensils and its lamps and the oil for the light;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2547L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2547L\"></sup>altar of incense and its poles, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2547M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2547M\"></sup>anointing oil and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2547N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2547N\"></sup>fragrant incense, and the screen for the doorway at the entrance of the tabernacle;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2548O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2548O\"></sup>the altar of burnt offering with its bronze grating, its poles, and all its utensils, the basin and its stand;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2549P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2549P\"></sup>the hangings of the court, its pillars and its sockets, and the screen for the gate of the court;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>the pegs of the tabernacle and the pegs of the court and their cords;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2551Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2551Q\"></sup>woven garments for ministering in the holy place, the holy garments for Aaron the priest and the garments of his sons, to minister as priests.’”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then all the congregation of the sons of Israel departed from Moses’ presence.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2553R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2553R\"></sup>Everyone whose heart stirred him and everyone whose spirit moved him came <i>and</i> brought the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> contribution for the work of the tent of meeting and for all its service and for the holy garments.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then all whose hearts moved them, both men and women, came <i>and</i> brought brooches and earrings and signet rings and bracelets, all articles of gold; so <i>did</i> every man who presented an offering of gold to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Every man, who had in his possession blue and purple and scarlet <i>material</i> and fine linen and goats’ <i>hair</i> and rams’ skins dyed red and porpoise skins, brought them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Everyone who could make a contribution of silver and bronze brought the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> contribution; and every man who had in his possession acacia wood for any work of the service brought it.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>All the skilled women spun with their hands, and brought what they had spun, <i>in</i> blue and purple <i>and</i> scarlet <i>material</i> and <i>in</i> fine linen.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>All the women whose heart stirred with a skill spun the goats’ <i>hair</i>.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The rulers brought the onyx stones and the stones for setting for the ephod and for the breastpiece;",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2560S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2560S\"></sup>the spice and the oil for the light and for the anointing oil and for the fragrant incense.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The Israelites, all the men and women, whose heart moved them to bring <i>material</i> for all the work, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded through Moses to be done, brought a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2561T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2561T\"></sup>freewill offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2562U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2562U\"></sup>Then Moses said to the sons of Israel, “See, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has called by name Bezalel the son of Uri, the son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>And He has filled him with the Spirit of God, in wisdom, in understanding and in knowledge and in all craftsmanship;",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>to make designs for working in gold and in silver and in bronze,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>and in the cutting of stones for settings and in the carving of wood, so as to perform in every inventive work.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>He also has put in his heart to teach, both he and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2566V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2566V\"></sup>Oholiab, the son of Ahisamach, of the tribe of Dan.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2567W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2567W\"></sup>He has filled them with skill to perform every work of an engraver and of a designer and of an embroiderer, in blue and in purple <i>and</i> in scarlet <i>material</i>, and in fine linen, and of a weaver, as performers of every work and makers of designs."
		},
		"36": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">36 </span>“Now Bezalel and Oholiab, and every skillful person in whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has put skill and understanding to know how to perform all the work in the construction of the sanctuary, shall perform in accordance with all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has commanded.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then Moses called Bezalel and Oholiab and every skillful person in whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had put skill, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2569A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2569A\"></sup>everyone whose heart stirred him, to come to the work to perform it.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They received from Moses all the contributions which the sons of Israel had brought to perform the work in the construction of the sanctuary. And they still <i>continued</i> bringing to him freewill offerings every morning.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And all the skillful men who were performing all the work of the sanctuary came, each from the work which he was performing,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and they said to Moses, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2572B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2572B\"></sup>The people are bringing much more than enough for the construction work which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> commanded <i>us</i> to perform.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Moses issued a command, and a proclamation was circulated throughout the camp, saying, “Let no man or woman any longer perform work for the contributions of the sanctuary.” Thus the people were restrained from bringing <i>any more</i>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2574C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2574C\"></sup>For the material they had was sufficient and more than enough for all the work, to perform it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2575D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2575D\"></sup>All the skillful men among those who were performing the work made the tabernacle with ten curtains; of fine twisted linen and blue and purple and scarlet <i>material</i>, with cherubim, the work of a skillful workman, Bezalel made them.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The length of each curtain was twenty-eight cubits and the width of each curtain four cubits; all the curtains had the same measurements.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>He joined five curtains to one another and <i>the other</i> five curtains he joined to one another.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He made loops of blue on the edge of the outermost curtain in the first set; he did likewise on the edge of the curtain that was outermost in the second set.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2579E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2579E\"></sup>fifty loops in the one curtain and he made fifty loops on the edge of the curtain that was in the second set; the loops were opposite each other.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2580F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2580F\"></sup>fifty clasps of gold and joined the curtains to one another with the clasps, so the tabernacle was a unit.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2581G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2581G\"></sup>he made curtains of goats’ <i>hair</i> for a tent over the tabernacle; he made eleven curtains in all.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The length of each curtain <i>was</i> thirty cubits and four cubits the width of each curtain; the eleven curtains had the same measurements.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He joined five curtains by themselves and <i>the other</i> six curtains by themselves.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Moreover, he made fifty loops on the edge of the curtain that was outermost in the <i>first</i> set, and he made fifty loops on the edge of the curtain <i>that was outermost in</i> the second set.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>He made fifty clasps of bronze to join the tent together so that it would be a unit.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He made a covering for the tent of rams’ skins dyed red, and a covering of porpoise skins above.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2587H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2587H\"></sup>Then he made the boards for the tabernacle of acacia wood, standing upright.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Ten cubits <i>was</i> the length of each board and one and a half cubits the width of each board.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><i>There were</i> two tenons for each board, fitted to one another; thus he did for all the boards of the tabernacle.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He made the boards for the tabernacle: twenty boards for the south side;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and he made forty sockets of silver under the twenty boards; two sockets under one board for its two tenons and two sockets under another board for its two tenons.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then for the second side of the tabernacle, on the north side, he made twenty boards,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and their forty sockets of silver; two sockets under one board and two sockets under another board.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>For the rear of the tabernacle, to the west, he made six boards.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He made two boards for the corners of the tabernacle at the rear.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>They were double beneath, and together they were complete to its top to the first ring; thus he did with both of them for the two corners.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>There were eight boards with their sockets of silver, sixteen sockets, two under every board.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then he made <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2598I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2598I\"></sup>bars of acacia wood, five for the boards of one side of the tabernacle,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>and five bars for the boards of the other side of the tabernacle, and five bars for the boards of the tabernacle for the rear <i>side</i> to the west.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He made the middle bar to pass through in the center of the boards from end to end.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>He overlaid the boards with gold and made their rings of gold <i>as</i> holders for the bars, and overlaid the bars with gold.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2602J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2602J\"></sup>Moreover, he made the veil of blue and purple and scarlet <i>material</i>, and fine twisted linen; he made it with cherubim, the work of a skillful workman.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>He made four pillars of acacia for it, and overlaid them with gold, with their hooks of gold; and he cast four sockets of silver for them.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>He made a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2604K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2604K\"></sup>screen for the doorway of the tent, of blue and purple and scarlet <i>material</i>, and fine twisted linen, the work of a weaver;",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>and <i>he made</i> its <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2605L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2605L\"></sup>five pillars with their hooks, and he overlaid their tops and their bands with gold; but their five sockets were of bronze."
		},
		"37": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">37 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2606A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2606A\"></sup>Now Bezalel made the ark of acacia wood; its length was two and a half cubits, and its width one and a half cubits, and its height one and a half cubits;",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>and he overlaid it with pure gold inside and out, and made a gold molding for it all around.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He cast four rings of gold for it on its four feet; even two rings on one side of it, and two rings on the other side of it.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He made poles of acacia wood and overlaid them with gold.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He put the poles into the rings on the sides of the ark, to carry it.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He made a mercy seat of pure gold, two and a half cubits long and one and a half cubits wide.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He made two cherubim of gold; he made them of hammered work at the two ends of the mercy seat;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>one cherub at the one end and one cherub at the other end; he made the cherubim <i>of one piece</i> with the mercy seat at the two ends.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The cherubim had <i>their</i> wings spread upward, covering the mercy seat with their wings, with their faces toward each other; the faces of the cherubim were toward the mercy seat.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2615B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2615B\"></sup>Then he made the table of acacia wood, two cubits long and a cubit wide and one and a half cubits high.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He overlaid it with pure gold, and made a gold molding for it all around.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>He made a rim for it of a handbreadth all around, and made a gold molding for its rim all around.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He cast four gold rings for it and put the rings on the four corners that were on its four feet.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Close by the rim were the rings, the holders for the poles to carry the table.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>He made the poles of acacia wood and overlaid them with gold, to carry the table.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>He made the utensils which were on the table, its dishes and its pans and its bowls and its jars, with which to pour out drink offerings, of pure gold.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2622C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2622C\"></sup>Then he made the lampstand of pure gold. He made the lampstand of hammered work, its base and its shaft; its cups, its bulbs and its flowers were <i>of one piece</i> with it.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>There were six branches going out of its sides; three branches of the lampstand from the one side of it and three branches of the lampstand from the other side of it;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>three cups shaped like almond <i>blossoms</i>, a bulb and a flower in one branch, and three cups shaped like almond <i>blossoms</i>, a bulb and a flower in the other branch—so for the six branches going out of the lampstand.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>In the lampstand <i>there were</i> four cups shaped like almond <i>blossoms</i>, its bulbs and its flowers;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>and a bulb was under the <i>first</i> pair of branches <i>coming</i> out of it, and a bulb under the <i>second</i> pair of branches <i>coming</i> out of it, and a bulb under the <i>third</i> pair of branches <i>coming</i> out of it, for the six branches coming out of the lampstand.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Their bulbs and their branches were <i>of one piece</i> with it; the whole of it <i>was</i> a single hammered work of pure gold.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He made its seven lamps with its snuffers and its trays of pure gold.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>He made it and all its utensils from a talent of pure gold.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2630D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2630D\"></sup>Then he made the altar of incense of acacia wood: a cubit long and a cubit wide, square, and two cubits high; its horns were <i>of one piece</i> with it.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>He overlaid it with pure gold, its top and its sides all around, and its horns; and he made a gold molding for it all around.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>He made two golden rings for it under its molding, on its two sides—on opposite sides—as holders for poles with which to carry it.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>He made the poles of acacia wood and overlaid them with gold.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2634E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2634E\"></sup>And he made the holy anointing oil and the pure, fragrant incense of spices, the work of a perfumer."
		},
		"38": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">38 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2635A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2635A\"></sup>Then he made the altar of burnt offering of acacia wood, five cubits long, and five cubits wide, square, and three cubits high.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He made its horns on its four corners, its horns being <i>of one piece</i> with it, and he overlaid it with bronze.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>He made all the utensils of the altar, the pails and the shovels and the basins, the flesh hooks and the firepans; he made all its utensils of bronze.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He made for the altar a grating of bronze network beneath, under its ledge, reaching halfway up.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>He cast four rings on the four ends of the bronze grating <i>as</i> holders for the poles.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He made the poles of acacia wood and overlaid them with bronze.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>He inserted the poles into the rings on the sides of the altar, with which to carry it. He made it hollow with planks.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2642B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2642B\"></sup>Moreover, he made the laver of bronze with its base of bronze, from the mirrors of the serving women who served at the doorway of the tent of meeting.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2643C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2643C\"></sup>Then he made the court: for the south side the hangings of the court were of fine twisted linen, one hundred cubits;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>their twenty pillars, and their twenty sockets, <i>made</i> of bronze; the hooks of the pillars and their bands <i>were</i> of silver.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>For the north side <i>there were</i> one hundred cubits; their twenty pillars and their twenty sockets <i>were</i> of bronze, the hooks of the pillars and their bands <i>were</i> of silver.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>For the west side <i>there were</i> hangings of fifty cubits <i>with</i> their ten pillars and their ten sockets; the hooks of the pillars and their bands <i>were</i> of silver.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>For the east side fifty cubits.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The hangings for the <i>one</i> side <i>of the gate were</i> fifteen cubits, <i>with</i> their three pillars and their three sockets,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and so for the other side. On both sides of the gate of the court <i>were</i> hangings of fifteen cubits, <i>with</i> their three pillars and their three sockets.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>All the hangings of the court all around <i>were</i> of fine twisted linen.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The sockets for the pillars <i>were</i> of bronze, the hooks of the pillars and their bands, of silver; and the overlaying of their tops, of silver, and all the pillars of the court were furnished with silver bands.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The screen of the gate of the court was the work of the weaver, of blue and purple and scarlet <i>material</i> and fine twisted linen. And the length <i>was</i> twenty cubits and the height <i>was</i> five cubits, corresponding to the hangings of the court.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Their four pillars and their four sockets <i>were</i> of bronze; their hooks <i>were</i> of silver, and the overlaying of their tops and their bands <i>were</i> of silver.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>All the pegs of the tabernacle and of the court all around <i>were</i> of bronze.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>This is the number of the things for the tabernacle, the tabernacle of the testimony, as they were numbered according to the command of Moses, for the service of the Levites, by the hand of Ithamar the son of Aaron the priest.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2656D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2656D\"></sup>Bezalel the son of Uri, the son of Hur, of the tribe of Judah, made all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>With him <i>was</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2657E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2657E\"></sup>Oholiab the son of Ahisamach, of the tribe of Dan, an engraver and a skillful workman and a weaver in blue and in purple and in scarlet <i>material</i>, and fine linen.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>All the gold that was used for the work, in all the work of the sanctuary, even the gold of the wave offering, was 29 talents and 730 shekels, according to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2658F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2658F\"></sup>the shekel of the sanctuary.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2659G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2659G\"></sup>The silver of those of the congregation who were numbered was 100 talents and 1,775 shekels, according to the shekel of the sanctuary;",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2660H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2660H\"></sup>a beka a head (<i>that is</i>, half a shekel according to the shekel of the sanctuary), for each one who passed over to those who were numbered, from twenty years old and upward, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2660I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2660I\"></sup>603,550 men.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The hundred talents of silver were for casting the sockets of the sanctuary and the sockets of the veil; one hundred sockets for the hundred talents, a talent for a socket.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Of the 1,775 <i>shekels</i>, he made hooks for the pillars and overlaid their tops and made bands for them.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The bronze of the wave offering was 70 talents and 2,400 shekels.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>With it he made the sockets to the doorway of the tent of meeting, and the bronze altar and its bronze grating, and all the utensils of the altar,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and the sockets of the court all around and the sockets of the gate of the court, and all the pegs of the tabernacle and all the pegs of the court all around."
		},
		"39": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">39 </span>Moreover, from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2666A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2666A\"></sup>blue and purple and scarlet <i>material</i>, they made finely <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2666B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2666B\"></sup>woven garments for ministering in the holy place as well as the holy garments which were for Aaron, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2667C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2667C\"></sup>He made the ephod of gold, <i>and</i> of blue and purple and scarlet <i>material</i>, and fine twisted linen.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then they hammered out gold sheets and cut <i>them</i> into threads to be woven in <i>with</i> the blue and the purple and the scarlet <i>material</i>, and the fine linen, the work of a skillful workman.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They made attaching shoulder pieces for the ephod; it was attached at its two <i>upper</i> ends.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The skillfully woven band which was on it was like its workmanship, of the same material: of gold <i>and</i> of blue and purple and scarlet <i>material</i>, and fine twisted linen, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2671D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2671D\"></sup>They made the onyx stones, set in gold filigree <i>settings</i>; they were engraved <i>like</i> the engravings of a signet, according to the names of the sons of Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2672E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2672E\"></sup>he placed them on the shoulder pieces of the ephod, <i>as</i> memorial stones for the sons of Israel, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2673F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2673F\"></sup>He made the breastpiece, the work of a skillful workman, like the workmanship of the ephod: of gold <i>and</i> of blue and purple and scarlet <i>material</i> and fine twisted linen.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>It was square; they made the breastpiece folded double, a span long and a span wide when folded double.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And they mounted four rows of stones on it. The first row <i>was</i> a row of ruby, topaz, and emerald;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>and the second row, a turquoise, a sapphire and a diamond;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and the third row, a jacinth, an agate, and an amethyst;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and the fourth row, a beryl, an onyx, and a jasper. They were set in gold filigree <i>settings</i> when they were mounted.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The stones were corresponding to the names of the sons of Israel; they were twelve, corresponding to their names, <i>engraved with</i> the engravings of a signet, each with its name for the twelve tribes.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They made on the breastpiece chains like cords, of twisted cordage work in pure gold.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>They made two gold filigree <i>settings</i> and two gold rings, and put the two rings on the two ends of the breastpiece.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then they put the two gold cords in the two rings at the ends of the breastpiece.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>They put the <i>other</i> two ends of the two cords on the two filigree <i>settings</i>, and put them on the shoulder pieces of the ephod at the front of it.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>They made two gold rings and placed <i>them</i> on the two ends of the breastpiece, on its inner edge which was next to the ephod.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Furthermore, they made two gold rings and placed them on the bottom of the two shoulder pieces of the ephod, on the front of it, close to the place where it joined, above the woven band of the ephod.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They bound the breastpiece by its rings to the rings of the ephod with a blue cord, so that it would be on the woven band of the ephod, and that the breastpiece would not come loose from the ephod, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2687G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2687G\"></sup>Then he made the robe of the ephod of woven work, all of blue;",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2688H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2688H\"></sup>and the opening of the robe was <i>at the top</i> in the center, as the opening of a coat of mail, with a binding all around its opening, so that it would not be torn.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>They made pomegranates of blue and purple and scarlet <i>material and</i> twisted <i>linen</i> on the hem of the robe.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>They also made bells of pure gold, and put the bells between the pomegranates all around on the hem of the robe,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>alternating a bell and a pomegranate all around on the hem of the robe for the service, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2692I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2692I\"></sup>They made the tunics of finely woven linen for Aaron and his sons,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and the turban of fine linen, and the decorated caps of fine linen, and the linen breeches of fine twisted linen,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>and the sash of fine twisted linen, and blue and purple and scarlet <i>material</i>, the work of the weaver, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2695J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2695J\"></sup>They made the plate of the holy crown of pure gold, and inscribed it like the engravings of a signet, “Holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>They fastened a blue cord to it, to fasten it on the turban above, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Thus all the work of the tabernacle of the tent of meeting was completed; and the sons of Israel did according to all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses; so they did.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>They brought the tabernacle to Moses, the tent and all its furnishings: its clasps, its boards, its bars, and its pillars and its sockets;",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>and the covering of rams’ skins dyed red, and the covering of porpoise skins, and the screening veil;",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>the ark of the testimony and its poles and the mercy seat;",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>the table, all its utensils, and the bread of the Presence;",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>the pure <i>gold</i> lampstand, with its arrangement of lamps and all its utensils, and the oil for the light;",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>and the gold altar, and the anointing oil and the fragrant incense, and the veil for the doorway of the tent;",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>the bronze altar and its bronze grating, its poles and all its utensils, the laver and its stand;",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>the hangings for the court, its pillars and its sockets, and the screen for the gate of the court, its cords and its pegs and all the equipment for the service of the tabernacle, for the tent of meeting;",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>the woven garments for ministering in the holy place and the holy garments for Aaron the priest and the garments of his sons, to minister as priests.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>So the sons of Israel did all the work according to all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And Moses examined all the work and behold, they had done it; just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded, this they had done. So Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2708K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2708K\"></sup>blessed them."
		},
		"40": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">40 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke to Moses, saying,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2710A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2710A\"></sup>On the first day of the first month you shall set up the tabernacle of the tent of meeting.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2711B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2711B\"></sup>You shall place the ark of the testimony there, and you shall screen the ark with the veil.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>You shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2712C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2712C\"></sup>bring in the table and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2712D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2712D\"></sup>arrange what belongs on it; and you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2712E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2712E\"></sup>bring in the lampstand and mount its lamps.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Moreover, you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2713F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2713F\"></sup>set the gold altar of incense before the ark of the testimony, and set up the veil for the doorway to the tabernacle.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>You shall set the altar of burnt offering in front of the doorway of the tabernacle of the tent of meeting.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2715G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2715G\"></sup>set the laver between the tent of meeting and the altar and put water in it.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>You shall set up the court all around and hang up the veil for the gateway of the court.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then you shall take the anointing oil and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2717H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2717H\"></sup>anoint the tabernacle and all that is in it, and shall consecrate it and all its furnishings; and it shall be holy.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You shall anoint the altar of burnt offering and all its utensils, and consecrate the altar, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2718I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2718I\"></sup>the altar shall be most holy.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>You shall anoint the laver and its stand, and consecrate it.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then you shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2720J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2720J\"></sup>bring Aaron and his sons to the doorway of the tent of meeting and wash them with water.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2721K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2721K\"></sup>You shall put the holy garments on Aaron and anoint him and consecrate him, that he may minister as a priest to Me.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You shall bring his sons and put tunics on them;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and you shall anoint them even as you have anointed their father, that they may minister as priests to Me; and their anointing will qualify them for a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2723L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2723L\"></sup>perpetual priesthood throughout their generations.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Thus Moses did; according to all that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded him, so he did.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2725M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2725M\"></sup>in the first month of the second year, on the first <i>day</i> of the month, the tabernacle was erected.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Moses erected the tabernacle and laid its sockets, and set up its boards, and inserted its bars and erected its pillars.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He spread the tent over the tabernacle and put the covering of the tent on top of it, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then he took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2728N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2728N\"></sup>the testimony and put <i>it</i> into the ark, and attached the poles to the ark, and put the mercy seat on top of the ark.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He brought the ark into the tabernacle, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2729O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2729O\"></sup>set up a veil for the screen, and screened off the ark of the testimony, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2730P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2730P\"></sup>put the table in the tent of meeting on the north side of the tabernacle, outside the veil.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He set the arrangement of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2731Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2731Q\"></sup>bread in order on it before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then he placed the lampstand in the tent of meeting, opposite the table, on the south side of the tabernacle.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2733R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2733R\"></sup>lighted the lamps before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2734S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2734S\"></sup>placed the gold altar in the tent of meeting in front of the veil;",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2735T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2735T\"></sup>burned fragrant incense on it, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Then he set up the veil for the doorway of the tabernacle.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2737U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2737U\"></sup>set the altar of burnt offering <i>before</i> the doorway of the tabernacle of the tent of meeting, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2737V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2737V\"></sup>offered on it the burnt offering and the meal offering, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>He placed the laver between the tent of meeting and the altar and put water in it for washing.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2739W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2739W\"></sup>From it Moses and Aaron and his sons washed their hands and their feet.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>When they entered the tent of meeting, and when they approached the altar, they washed, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Moses.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>He <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2741X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2741X\"></sup>erected the court all around the tabernacle and the altar, and hung up the veil for the gateway of the court. Thus Moses finished the work.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2742Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2742Y\"></sup>Then the cloud covered the tent of meeting, and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2742Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2742Z\"></sup>glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> filled the tabernacle.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2743AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2743AA\"></sup>was not able to enter the tent of meeting because the cloud had settled on it, and the glory of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> filled the tabernacle.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Throughout all their journeys <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2744AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2744AB\"></sup>whenever the cloud was taken up from over the tabernacle, the sons of Israel would set out;",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2745AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2745AC\"></sup>if the cloud was not taken up, then they did not set out until the day when it was taken up.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>For throughout all their journeys, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-2746AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-2746AD\"></sup>the cloud of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was on the tabernacle by day, and there was fire in it by night, in the sight of all the house of Israel."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;